{"id": "41887", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41887", "title": "Challenge of the Immortal", "text": "The Challenge of the Immortal is the culmination of the &lt;a href=\"Cycle%20of%20Strife\"&gt;Cycle of Strife&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nThe Challenge of the Immortal is a PvP feature in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". After the conclusion of the &lt;a href=\"Rite%20of%20Exile\"&gt;Rite of Exile&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Shadows\"&gt;Shadows&lt;/a&gt; who won will move onto the Challenge. Here, 30 Shadows are pitted against a single &lt;a href=\"Immortal\"&gt;Immortal&lt;/a&gt;. The Immortal player is the top Immortal player on the server, and will be transformed into a giant raid boss. The Immortal player gains unique skills, and is so powerful they can one-shot Shadow players.\nIf the Immortal defeats all the Shadows, their reign continues. If the Shadows win, they are resurrected and move onto &lt;a href=\"The%20Final%20Battle\"&gt;The Final Battle&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn week 7 of the &lt;a href=\"Cycle%20of%20Strife\"&gt;Cycle of Strife&lt;/a&gt;, if the Immortal manages to win, a short cutscene plays in which &lt;a href=\"Kion\"&gt;Kion&lt;/a&gt; offers the Eternal Crown to the Immortal again, only for &lt;a href=\"Akeba\"&gt;Akeba&lt;/a&gt; to steal it and order the Shadows to fight for it.\nHistory.\nThe format of Challenge of the Immortal used to be used for the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20War\"&gt;Shadow War&lt;/a&gt;, with the clan leaders taking the role of the Immortal on the opposing clan's side and no free-for-all battle afterwards, until it was replaced by the &lt;a href=\"Alley%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Alley of Blood&lt;/a&gt; format in the September 21 2023 update.\nIn the update, the number of kills required for the Immortal to win was reduced."}
