{"id": "38873", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38873", "title": "Challenging Shout", "text": "Challenging Shout\u00a0is a Defensive skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", combining the elements of , &lt;a href=\"Provoke\"&gt;Provoke&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ignore%20Pain\"&gt;Ignore Pain&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThis skill does not bestow any extra &lt;a href=\"Absorption\"&gt;Absorption&lt;/a&gt; on the Barbarian, but instead reduces damage taken until specified amount of Life is lost from attacks: that is, until the fortified Life is depleted (or until the timer runs out), any incoming damage will be reduced by 30%. Does not affect allies.\nExtra gain does not depend on the source of the attack: if any Fury is generated from taking damage, automatically adds another +5 to it.\nCounts as Shout and Warlord skill."}
