{"id": "3701", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3701", "title": "Cham Rune", "text": "A Cham rune is a high &lt;a href=\"Runes\"&gt;rune&lt;/a&gt; which can be &lt;a href=\"socket\"&gt;socket&lt;/a&gt;ed into equipment in \"\". The few rune words using Cham are not particularly popular, but Cham runes remain valuable for their &lt;a href=\"Cannot%20Be%20Frozen\"&gt;Cannot Be Frozen&lt;/a&gt; property, and for their rarity as a rune, second only to Zod.\nEffects.\nSocketing an item with a Cham rune increases the item's level requirement to 67, unless it was already higher.\nA Cham rune is one of only a handful of sources of the &lt;a href=\"Cannot%20Be%20Frozen\"&gt;Cannot Be Frozen&lt;/a&gt; attribute, important for protecting heroes reliant on attack speed from being &lt;a href=\"slow\"&gt;chilled&lt;/a&gt;. Socketing a Cham rune in a helm, shield or armor can free up an equipment slot normally dedicated to getting Cannot Be Frozen, such as a ring slot for &lt;a href=\"Raven%20Frost\"&gt;Raven Frost&lt;/a&gt;, for a more offensive option.\nSources.\nThe Act 4 (H) Good treasure class has a chance to drop a Cham rune, as does the Act 5 (H) Good treasure class.\nIn single-player, open or ladder games only, the &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; can transmute two &lt;a href=\"Jah%20Rune\"&gt;Jah runes&lt;/a&gt; and one flawless ruby into one Cham rune.\nRune Words.\nCham runes are used in these &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;rune words&lt;/a&gt;:\nRecipes.\nCham runes are used in one &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; recipe."}
