{"id": "42015", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42015", "title": "Chamber of Truth", "text": "The Chamber of Truth is a structure located in the &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;. It sits atop the &lt;a href=\"Prison%20of%20the%20Scorpion\"&gt;Prison of the Scorpion&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Amber%20Blades\"&gt;Amber Blades&lt;/a&gt; traveled here to meet with a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt;, who accompanied a piece of the &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;Scepter of Fahir&lt;/a&gt; from the Prison of the Scorpion.\nIn-game.\nThe Chamber of Truth is located in the &lt;a href=\"Oasis%20of%20No%20Return\"&gt;Oasis of No Return&lt;/a&gt;. It is effectively a sub-zone, giving way to the Prison of the Scorpion."}
{"id": "41947", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41947", "title": "Chamber of Wisdom", "text": "The Chamber of Wisdom is a structure located in the &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nThe structure has an inner and outer chamber. Entering the latter requires &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s to be channeled through a pair of braziers. The &lt;a href=\"Immortals\"&gt;Immortals&lt;/a&gt; established a safehouse in/beneath the chamber.\nHistory.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Fahir\"&gt;Fahir&lt;/a&gt;'s reign, a mass sacrifice was held in the chamber\u20141000 individuals were sacrificed in &lt;a href=\"Fahir\"&gt;Fahir&lt;/a&gt;'s name. After Fahir's death, &lt;a href=\"Fahir%27s%20Command\"&gt;one&lt;/a&gt; of the three pieces of his &lt;a href=\"Scepter%20of%20Fahir\"&gt;scepter&lt;/a&gt; was sealed here.\nOver the ages, many adventurers died searching for the scepter pieces, but perished. Apparently, some perished at the hands of &lt;a href=\"Corphet\"&gt;Corphet&lt;/a&gt; himself (the chamber's guardian).\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; entered the structure to find the scepter piece, per the directions of &lt;a href=\"Tabri\"&gt;Tabri&lt;/a&gt;. Inside, however, they were ambushed by &lt;a href=\"Valla\"&gt;Valla&lt;/a&gt;, who are promptly destroying some &lt;a href=\"skeleton\"&gt;skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s, realized that they weren't a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;. She let them free, and advised that they leave\u2014advice that they didn't take. They slew Corphet and took the scepter piece.\n&lt;a href=\"Timeline%231273\"&gt;Three years later&lt;/a&gt;, some Amber Blades entered the chamber to investigate deep rumblings that had been heard from underground. The interior showed signs of being cursed: the light was different like it was being filtered through smoke, but nothing was burning; the ground felt of mush and the air smelled so iof rot that it was difficult to breathe. As they entered the rumblings stopped. When the Blades were deep into the chamber they heard a voice like tearing leather, ordering them to run or submit. They ran.\nIn-game.\nThe Chamber of Wisdom is a Shassar Sea zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is located west of the &lt;a href=\"Lacuni%20Incursion\"&gt;Lacuni Incursion&lt;/a&gt;. It is here that the first scepter fragment is found, &lt;a href=\"Fahir%27s%20Command\"&gt;Fahir's Command&lt;/a&gt;. Exiting the dungeon will take players to the &lt;a href=\"Oasis%20of%20No%20Return\"&gt;Oasis of No Return&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Chamber is the location of an Immortals safehouse, featuring in the &lt;a href=\"contract\"&gt;contract&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Artful%20Replacement\"&gt;Artful Replacement&lt;/a&gt;.\""}
