{"id": "18925", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18925", "title": "Chancellor's Tomb", "text": "The Chancellor's Tomb is a location in &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", in which the players visits during the quest &lt;a href=\"A%20Shattered%20Crown\"&gt;A Shattered Crown&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is the tomb of &lt;a href=\"Chancellor%20Eamon\"&gt;Chancellor Eamon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"King%20Leoric\"&gt;King Leoric&lt;/a&gt;'s former chancellor. After Leoric's betrayal, Eamon locked himself in his tomb with &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Crown\"&gt;Leoric's Crown&lt;/a&gt;, to protect the citizens of &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe player must visit the tomb in order to retrieve Leoric's Crown, which is needed to defeat the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20King\"&gt;Skeleton King&lt;/a&gt; for the last time."}
{"id": "17486", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17486", "title": "Chancellor Eamon", "text": "Chancellor Eamon, Astral Guardian, is a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique\"&gt;Super Unique&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Wraith%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Wraith&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He is the spirit of &lt;a href=\"Haedrig%20Eamon\"&gt;Haedrig Eamon&lt;/a&gt;'s grandfather,\nBiography.\nBefore heading for &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt;, Eamon had a son, who in turn had a &lt;a href=\"Haedrig%20Eamon\"&gt;son of his own&lt;/a&gt;. They were living in &lt;a href=\"Caldeum\"&gt;Caldeum&lt;/a&gt; when Eamon left with &lt;a href=\"Leoric\"&gt;Leoric&lt;/a&gt; and his forces to journey to &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt;, where Leoric set up his seat of power in &lt;a href=\"Tristram\"&gt;Tristram&lt;/a&gt;. During the &lt;a href=\"Darkening%20of%20Tristram\"&gt;Darkening of Tristram&lt;/a&gt;, Eamon remained in the town, trying to save lives. \nAs Leoric descended further into madness, he ordered Eamon to seal the &lt;a href=\"Caverns%20of%20Araneae\"&gt;caves&lt;/a&gt; near his &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Manor\"&gt;manor&lt;/a&gt;, in order to protect his estate from the \"traitorous rabble\" in Tristram. He informed him that &lt;a href=\"Archbishop%20Lazarus\"&gt;Archbishop Lazarus&lt;/a&gt; had bound some &lt;a href=\"spider\"&gt;spider&lt;/a&gt;s to his will, and ordered the caverns filled with them. Eamon was unable to get the king to change his mind, and sorrowfully ordered the Royal Guard to obey the king's command, desecrating the ruins within the caverns.\nWhen Leoric was killed by his &lt;a href=\"Knights%20of%20Khanduras\"&gt;knights&lt;/a&gt;, Eamon was dying from a &lt;a href=\"swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; wound. He was buried in a &lt;a href=\"Chancellor%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;tomb&lt;/a&gt; and had &lt;a href=\"Leoric%27s%20Crown\"&gt;Leoric's Crown&lt;/a&gt; sealed with him.\nOver &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231285\"&gt;twenty years later&lt;/a&gt;, Eamon was resurrected (likely as a result of the &lt;a href=\"Tyrael\"&gt;Fallen Star&lt;/a&gt;. He was confronted by &lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;, who sought Leoric's crown. Eamon tried to prevent them from claiming it, but failed, dying a second time. The crown was broken, and The Nephalem wondered if Eamon had done this himself, to prevent anyone from abusing it. Neverthless, the crown was reforged.\nIn-game.\nEamon is found in the &lt;a href=\"Chancellor%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Chancellor's Tomb&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He protects Leoric's Crown, an item the player has to recover in order to defeat the &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20King\"&gt;Skeleton King&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0during the quest \"&lt;a href=\"A%20Shattered%20Crown\"&gt;A Shattered Crown&lt;/a&gt;.\" The crown may not be taken until Chancellor Eamon is defeated.\nHis attack has a very potent Slow on every hit. In addition, he has Knockback and Teleporter affixes."}
