{"id": "33761", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33761", "title": "Charm (Diablo III)", "text": ""}
{"id": "53070", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53070", "title": "Charm (Diablo Immortal)", "text": "Charms are a type of equipment in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;.\nGameplay.\nCharms can be obtained from various rewards such as getting 70 &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Points\"&gt;Battle Points&lt;/a&gt; per day as well as &lt;a href=\"Battleground\"&gt;Battleground&lt;/a&gt; weekly rewards.\nA basic charm has a single skill bonus on it that can be for any class. Basic charms can be salvaged for alchemical powder, which can then be used to upgrade other charms. An upgraded charm gains additional skill bonuses, however the skills are chosen at random and may be of different classes. Upgraded charms cannot be salvaged.\nA rank 5 charm can be extracted for 500 &lt;a href=\"Platinum\"&gt;Platinum&lt;/a&gt;, resulting in a Skill Stone that can be sold on the &lt;a href=\"Market%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Market&lt;/a&gt;. A Skill Stone can be Imbued into a charm. This is done by first selecting a particular skill on the charm, then selecting the skill stone. A random skill is then chosen from the skill stone. The player can choose to replace the skill on the charm with the randomly chosen one or keep the original skill. The stone is lost in either case. When imbuing the skill, it has a chance to provide a higher bonus than the default 2%, up to 10%.\nVanguard.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Vanguard\"&gt;Vanguard&lt;/a&gt; event has its special set of charms, see &lt;a href=\"Vanguard%20Charms\"&gt;Vanguard Charms&lt;/a&gt; for details.\nHistory.\nIn the update, a lock feature was added to Charms to prevent accidental destruction."}
{"id": "27994", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27994", "title": "Charm (Focus)", "text": "The Charm is an &lt;a href=\"Enchantress%20Focuses\"&gt;Enchantress Focus&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"Eirena\"&gt;Eirena&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt requires character level 23 to be used."}
{"id": "27523", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27523", "title": "Charm (effect)", "text": "Charms\u00a0are a type of spell. It is also a potent type of &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt; effect.\nLore.\nThe Charm spell makes the victim think (for a short time) that the caster is their closest friend, or even beloved one, and unable to resist them in any way or just part with them. &lt;a href=\"Eirena\"&gt;Eirena&lt;/a&gt; once accidentally cast this spell on &lt;a href=\"Lysa\"&gt;Lysa&lt;/a&gt;, causing the latter to follow her fanatically for a forthnight. When &lt;a href=\"Lyndon\"&gt;Lyndon&lt;/a&gt; attempted to flirt with Eirena by asking her how did she become so good at 'charming' others, she took his words literally, saying that she practiced this spell times beyond count.\nIn-game.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", the &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Conversion\"&gt;Conversion&lt;/a&gt; skill functions similarly to Charm.\nCharm is a &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;al effect in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", mostly used by Eirena (as well as &lt;a href=\"Lysa\"&gt;Lysa&lt;/a&gt;). The other notable Charming effects are those of &lt;a href=\"The%20Tormentor\"&gt;The Tormentor&lt;/a&gt; staff, &lt;a href=\"Henri%27s%20Perquisition\"&gt;Henri's Perquisition&lt;/a&gt; mojo and &lt;a href=\"Overwhelming%20Desire\"&gt;Overwhelming Desire&lt;/a&gt; amulet. s can also use it, via &lt;a href=\"skill%20rune\"&gt;skill rune&lt;/a&gt;s of skills like . s can intimidate their foes into submission as well, with &lt;a href=\"Skull%20of%20Resonance\"&gt;Skull of Resonance&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Overwhelming Desire amulet causes charmed enemies to take 35% more damage. This effect is not shared by other charms, even if Overwhelming Desire is equipped.\nFor gameplay purposes, Charm makes the affected enemy briefly fight on the caster's side, attacking their foes and unable to perform any offensive actions against the caster (and their allies). If Charmed while there are no other enemies around, the victim will just stand idle or follow the caster. While charmed, the other enemies will see the victim as a hostile target, and the caster's allies may still attack that target at will. Target's special abilities and skills may still be used, and will benefit the caster, or at least bring them no harm. This way, Charm is a more potent effect than &lt;a href=\"Confusion\"&gt;Confusion&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt; resistance reduces the duration of Charm. &lt;a href=\"Boss\"&gt;Boss&lt;/a&gt;es are immune to it.\nUnlike Confusion, Charm could initially affect players as well as monsters. In the released game, it can no longer affect players, even if they somehow manage to put such an effect on another player in &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "27521", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=27521", "title": "Charm spell", "text": ""}
{"id": "1760", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1760", "title": "Charms", "text": "Charms are accessory items found in \"\". These items only need to be present in the character's &lt;a href=\"inventory\"&gt;inventory&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Identify\"&gt;identified&lt;/a&gt; for their magical attributes to take effect. They do not function if placed inside your character's &lt;a href=\"Stash\"&gt;Stash&lt;/a&gt; or inside a &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt; (even if that Horadric Cube is located in your inventory).\nGenerally, smaller is actually better as far as Charms are concerned, since more can be stored in a player's inventory. However, some &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; es and es are only available on the larger Charms. There are also a few affixes that are actually more effective on Grand Charms than they are on Small Charms (+Attack Rating, for example).\nWhen using Charms, the player may really dig themselves into a hole wherein they cannot pick up any more items. It is best to pick only the best Charms to keep and sell ones that are sub-par. Try to keep some space to pick up one or two large items. Players are welcome to completely fill their inventory with Charms, but take note that other party members may pick up good equipment dropped by monsters.\nA Charm's effects are varied, some ranging from increasing one's &lt;a href=\"life\"&gt;life&lt;/a&gt; to even increasing the amount of &lt;a href=\"Gold\"&gt;Gold&lt;/a&gt; enemies drop upon &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;. It is advisable to store Life or &lt;a href=\"Resistance\"&gt;Resistance&lt;/a&gt; Charms in your Stash and equip them before facing a tough boss. Grand charms can even grant bonus to the entire &lt;a href=\"skill%20tree\"&gt;skill tree&lt;/a&gt;. They are known as &lt;a href=\"skiller\"&gt;skiller&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCharms come in varying sizes, each size having three types of artwork, which isn't in any way related to their stats:\nThere are only two types of Charms: &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Charms\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Crafted%20Items\"&gt;crafted&lt;/a&gt; charms have not been introduced. Magic Charms contain 2 attributes at most, which increase in quality depending on the size of the charm.\nCharms are a sort of collector's item in Diablo II. It brings a subtle strategy in the game by forcing item searchers to decide between increased stats versus inventory space."}
{"id": "29265", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29265", "title": "Charok", "text": "Charok is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Exorcist\"&gt;Exorcist&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He appears and must be killed for the &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Misfire\"&gt;Magic Misfire&lt;/a&gt; event, which takes place in the &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer%27s%20Room\"&gt;Sorcerer's Room&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn combat, he has &lt;a href=\"Orbiter\"&gt;Orbiter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Electrified\"&gt;Electrified&lt;/a&gt; traits."}
{"id": "53170", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53170", "title": "Charred Deceiver", "text": ""}
{"id": "1458", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1458", "title": "Charsi", "text": "Charsi is a blacksmith.\nBiography.\nEarly Life.\nWhen she was very young, Charsi and her parents were ambushed by a throng of &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt;. Her parents managed to hide her in the surrounding wilderness area before they were slaughtered. By chance, members of the &lt;a href=\"Sisterhood%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisterhood of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt; found Charsi and took her into their care. &lt;a href=\"Akara\"&gt;Akara&lt;/a&gt; then told Charsi what had happened to her parents.\nShe became a member of the Sisterhood, using her immense physical strength to forge the Order's &lt;a href=\"Weapons\"&gt;weaponry&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, wielding the &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Malus\"&gt;Horadric Malus&lt;/a&gt; to carry out her work. She became close friends with the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Rogue&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Moreina\"&gt;Moreina&lt;/a&gt;. \nWhile she enjoyed being a blacksmith, she sometimes wondered what her life would have been like if she had been raised as a &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt; instead. She believed that her real family was among the tribes of the &lt;a href=\"Northern%20Steppes\"&gt;Northern Steppes&lt;/a&gt;. Sometimes, she just wanted to get out and explore the &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;world&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Sightless Eye.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;1264&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Eastgate%20Keep\"&gt;Eastgate Keep&lt;/a&gt; fell to &lt;a href=\"Andariel\"&gt;Andariel&lt;/a&gt;, with many &lt;a href=\"Rogue\"&gt;Rogue&lt;/a&gt;s &lt;a href=\"Corrupt%20Rogue\"&gt;corrupted and turned&lt;/a&gt; to her side as a result. Charsi, and the other members of the Sisterhood, fled the &lt;a href=\"Eastgate%20Keep\"&gt;keep&lt;/a&gt;. In the chaos of retreat, Charsi left behind the Horadric Malus. She and the survivors established an &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Encampment\"&gt;encampment&lt;/a&gt; in the wilderness of &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt;. She was the youngest survivor of Eastgate. While in the camp, she continued to forge weapons and armor, taking satisfaction in the knowledge that they were helping to end the evil that plagued the land.\nSome newcomers arrived in the camp, among whom was &lt;a href=\"Gheed\"&gt;Gheed&lt;/a&gt;. Charsi liked him, and the stories of adventures that he told to her. She even let him guard her &lt;a href=\"Gold\"&gt;money&lt;/a&gt;.\nMore notably, a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; arrived in the camp, and slew Moreina &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Raven\"&gt;Blood Raven&lt;/a&gt;, who had fallen to Andariel's corruption. Charsi thanked them for putting her former friend to rest. The heroes are also be able to retrieve the Malus from Eastgate, and slay Andariel herself. Charsi wished them all well before they headed east.\nWestmarch.\nAfter the reclamation of Eastgate, Charsi became discontent with her life in the Sisterhood, apparently inspired by the heroes she had aided. She decided to leave the Sisterhood. When she left, &lt;a href=\"Akara\"&gt;Akara&lt;/a&gt; gave her an amulet that would open a portal to the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;, in case she ever needed to find her way home.\nCharsi became a blacksmith in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. Charsi's earlier deeds made her \"a legend,\" and business was good. Adventurers would bring material from the city's &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Rift\"&gt;Elder Rift&lt;/a&gt; to her &lt;a href=\"Charsi%27s%20Smithy\"&gt;smithy&lt;/a&gt;, giving her a steady income. She never entered the rift herself, however.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; arrived in the city, and asked her and &lt;a href=\"Piri\"&gt;Piri&lt;/a&gt; to greet a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; who he was expecting. Charsi was unable to leave her &lt;a href=\"Charsi%27s%20Smithy\"&gt;smithy&lt;/a&gt;, but Piri directed the hero(es) to her. Upon their arrival, Charsi directed them to Cain's workshop, promising that she'd give them a tour of Westmarch later.\nCharsi met the Shard-seeker outside Cain's workshop, learning that they hadn't destroyed the shards. They told her that they were headed for the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;, and at their request, Charsi took them to see the &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Rift\"&gt;Elder Rift&lt;/a&gt;. She later took them to see &lt;a href=\"Vic\"&gt;Vic&lt;/a&gt;, who she believed could help them with &lt;a href=\"legendary%20gems\"&gt;legendary gems&lt;/a&gt;. The two assisted Vic after he was accousted by some bandits.\nWhile the Shard-seeker was away, the city's was activated. &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;Adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s entered the Rift and brought materials back to Charsi's smithy.\nThe Shard-seeker returned from the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt;, and brought the regards of &lt;a href=\"Kashya\"&gt;Kashya&lt;/a&gt;, much to Charsi's joy. She took them to see the Challenge Rift, and told them to meet her at her smithy when they were done. There, she gave them a belt in thanks for them aiding the Sisterhood.\nLater Events.\nCharsi became aware of the &lt;a href=\"Domain%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Domain of Horror&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"Deceiver\"&gt;Deceiver&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s that lurked within it. She offered a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; to adventurers to enter the realm, slay the Deceivers, and bring their weapons to her. She hoped that studying them would aid in the fight against Hell. Similarly, she offered payment to those who could deliver her &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Steel%20%28Item%29\"&gt;Ashwold steel&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhen the Shard-seeker was away, Charsi met &lt;a href=\"Rayek\"&gt;Rayek&lt;/a&gt;. The two of them built the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;. Later, they came to Charsi to obtain some &lt;a href=\"scoria\"&gt;scoria&lt;/a&gt;, in order to reinforce the device. Charsi obliged, giving them the last of her supply.\nCharsi was among the friends that saw Deckard Cain off when he departed from Westmarch in &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;.\nC. &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231273\"&gt;1273&lt;/a&gt;, Rayek gave Charsi the blueprint for a strange device for her to build for him.\nReign of Enmity.\nCharsi was still alive duri of the &lt;a href=\"Reign%20of%20Enmity\"&gt;Reign of Enmity&lt;/a&gt;, but she had left Westmarch.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nCharsi is the blacksmith in the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Encampment\"&gt;Rogue Encampment&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", and is highly skilled at shaping, crafting and &lt;a href=\"repair\"&gt;repair&lt;/a&gt;ing weapons. During the chaos of the attack by the forces of &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; on the Rogue Monastery, she was forced to leave her most important forging tool behind, the . Fortunately for her, however, the hero returns the to her after defeating . With it, Charsi will imbue any &lt;a href=\"Normal%20Items\"&gt;normal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt; of the player's choice as a token of thanks.\nCharsi is very good-natured, and described as a \"sweet girl\" and \"young and innocent.\" She is highly accepting of the hero upon his/her entrance to the camp. She has a cheerful tone and is willing to help out a great deal. She shows a certain fondness toward most, even &lt;a href=\"Gheed\"&gt;Gheed&lt;/a&gt;, but feels that &lt;a href=\"Warriv\"&gt;Warriv&lt;/a&gt; is \"too quiet.\"\nHer ancestry is &lt;a href=\"Barbarian\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt;. She is a member of the &lt;a href=\"Sisterhood%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisterhood of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt;, evidenced when she refers to the Rogues as \"our sisters.\"\nDialogue.\nGossip about Charsi.\nSome of the other locals give their thoughts concerning Charsi.\nDiablo Immortal.\nCharsi is a vendor in Westmarch in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Players are first introduced her during the \"&lt;a href=\"Cain%27s%20Request\"&gt;Cain's Request&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. She later guides players through the city in a series of mini-quests. She will fight the &lt;a href=\"Brigand\"&gt;Brigand&lt;/a&gt;s in the \"&lt;a href=\"Diamond%20in%20the%20Rough\"&gt;Diamond in the Rough&lt;/a&gt;\" quest, but deals minimal damage.\nShe is the provider of the \"&lt;a href=\"Weapons%20of%20War\"&gt;Weapons of War&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Steel\"&gt;Ashwold Steel&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt;, and introduces players to the &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; in its questline, beginning with the quest \"&lt;a href=\"Opening%20the%20Helliquary\"&gt;Opening the Helliquary&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nCharsi can refine &lt;a href=\"Scoria\"&gt;Scoria&lt;/a&gt; for the player, converting it into &lt;a href=\"Hellfire%20Scoria\"&gt;Hellfire Scoria&lt;/a&gt;.\nPersonality and Traits.\nNaive but ebullient, Charsi takes great pride in her work, able to \"fashion any weapon of war.\" She loves hearing stories of adventure. &lt;a href=\"Akara\"&gt;Akara&lt;/a&gt; described Charsi as being \"young and innocent,\" but noted that her \"&lt;a href=\"Barbarian\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt;\" gave her the yearning for adventure and danger. &lt;a href=\"Gheed\"&gt;Gheed&lt;/a&gt; noted that Charsi has no business savvy.\nCharsi is aware of the existence of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Burning Hells&lt;/a&gt;, and is committed to the fight against it."}
