{"id": "18992", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=18992", "title": "Chiltara", "text": "Chiltara, The Vile Frost Stalker is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; female &lt;a href=\"Lacuni%20Huntress\"&gt;Wintersbane Huntress&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; of\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". When she is present in a game session, she can be found in the &lt;a href=\"Caverns%20of%20Frost\"&gt;Caverns of Frost&lt;/a&gt;, which are accessed from the &lt;a href=\"Fields%20of%20Slaughter\"&gt;Fields of Slaughter&lt;/a&gt;.\nShe is best known for having a low chance to drop the &lt;a href=\"Gibbering%20Gemstone\"&gt;Gibbering Gemstone&lt;/a&gt;, the only monster which does so. The Gemstone is required to craft the &lt;a href=\"Staff%20of%20Herding\"&gt;Staff of Herding&lt;/a&gt; and gain access to &lt;a href=\"Whimsyshire\"&gt;Whimsyshire&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn combat, she has &lt;a href=\"Orbiter\"&gt;Orbiter&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20%28monster%20trait%29\"&gt;Frozen&lt;/a&gt; traits.\nBefore &lt;a href=\"Patch%202.0.6%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Patch 2.0.6&lt;/a&gt;, in addition to the gemstone, she also had a chance to drop either a &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Blood\"&gt;Frozen Blood&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Urn%20of%20Quickening\"&gt;Urn of Quickening&lt;/a&gt;. The patch removed these items along with all other unique crafting materials.\nAvailability.\nShe only spawns in Caverns of Frost Level 2, which are not guaranteed to be present - the &lt;a href=\"Icefall%20Caves\"&gt;Icefall Caves&lt;/a&gt; may appear instead. Chiltara herself is also not guaranteed to spawn, and does not guarantee a drop of the Gibbering Gemstone. &lt;a href=\"Zelusa%20the%20Grasping\"&gt;Zelusa the Grasping&lt;/a&gt;, another Unique of the same type, spawns in the same area but does not prevent Chiltara from spawning also.\nAs of &lt;a href=\"Patch%202.4.1%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Patch 2.4.1&lt;/a&gt; it appears that she spawns a large percentage of time, but getting the gemstone to drop has a very low percentage. She usually appears right at the end of the cave, be it by the &lt;a href=\"Resplendent%20Chest\"&gt;Resplendent Chest&lt;/a&gt;, the Teleporting Stone or in a dead end tunnel."}
