{"id": "2597", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2597", "title": "Chris Metzen", "text": "Chris Vincent Metzen alias Thundergod is a member of &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe is also part of the &lt;a href=\"Sons%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Sons of the Storm&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nMetzen was the Vice President of Creative Development at Blizzard. He was responsible for most of the storylines and lore (through instruction manuals, etc.) found in the \"&lt;a href=\"Warcraft\"&gt;Warcraft&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"StarCraft\"&gt;StarCraft&lt;/a&gt;\" series of games as well as concept art and character design.\nMetzen was recruited by Blizzard in 1994, at the age of 19. At the time, he had expected to bounce between jobs in the comics, games, and film industries. However, the ability of the videogame medium to focus on multiple genres and generate a variety of ideas compelled him to stay in the industry.\nMetzen pioneered the idea of Blizzard's \"strike teams,\" which provided internal feedback to the company's development teams. This was part of an effort to keep the company's original development culture together.\nMetzen worked with Blizzard's cinematic team, and gave feedback on its storyboards. \nMetzen left Blizzard in late 2016, entering retirement. During this period, he briefly worked with Frost Giant Studios on the development of \"&lt;a href=\"https%3A//stormgate.fandom.com/wiki/Stormgate\"&gt;Stormgate&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nOn December 15, 2022 it was announced that Metzen had returned to the company to serve as a creative advisor for \"Warcraft\".\nDiablo Related Works.\nThe fictional universe of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" was created by both Metzen and fellow designer &lt;a href=\"Bill%20Roper\"&gt;Bill Roper&lt;/a&gt;. He developed the game's story. Prior to Metzen working on the game, there was little in the way of backstory or lore.\nMetzen also provided voice acting for some of the game's characters. \nMetzen continued his work on the \"Diablo\" series in 2000 on \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", where he worked on the game's story, script, and artwork. He offered feedback on &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20North\"&gt;Blizzard North&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III%20%28Blizzard%20North%29\"&gt;version&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", and developed the story of &lt;a href=\"Team%203\"&gt;Team 3&lt;/a&gt;'s version.\nGames.\n&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "34526", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=34526", "title": "Chris Millar", "text": "Chris Millar is a former member of &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;.\nHe worked on \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"StarCraft\"&gt;StarCraft&lt;/a&gt;\". He left Blizzard in the early 2000s. \nHe is now the head of &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fun_Bits_Interactive\"&gt;Fun Bits Interactive&lt;/a&gt;."}
