{"id": "6109", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6109", "title": "Chromatic Ire", "text": "The Chromatic Ire is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Weapons\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Exceptional%20Items\"&gt;exceptional&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Cedar%20Staff\"&gt;Cedar Staff&lt;/a&gt; that is found in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" and is designed for use by a &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;.\nIts Sorceress skill bonus is impressive, and gives equal treatment to all three of her skill trees. Although tri-elemental sorceresses are rare to find, those that do pursue that course can benefit from the bonuses to &lt;a href=\"Cold%20Mastery\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Mastery\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Mastery\"&gt;Lightning Mastery&lt;/a&gt; that the Chromatic Ire bestows. \nWhile it is good for all-round use, the Chromatic Ire may not be as useful to sorceresses that specialize in specific skill trees. For instance, Sorceresses that specialize in &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Spells\"&gt;Fire Spells&lt;/a&gt; may find a staff such as &lt;a href=\"The%20Salamander\"&gt;The Salamander&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"Leaf%20Rune%20Word\"&gt;Leaf Rune Word&lt;/a&gt; more useful, and Sorceresses that specialize in &lt;a href=\"Energy%20Shield\"&gt;Energy Shield&lt;/a&gt; would benefit far more from &lt;a href=\"Warpspear\"&gt;Warpspear&lt;/a&gt;. Additionally, more &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Items\"&gt;elite&lt;/a&gt; unique staves such as &lt;a href=\"Mang%20Song%27s%20Lesson\"&gt;Mang Song's Lesson&lt;/a&gt; may provide higher skill bonuses to all skills anyway. However, Mang Song's Lesson is available only on the &lt;a href=\"Ladder\"&gt;Ladder&lt;/a&gt;, keeping Chromatic Ire as a viable option for more frugal players.\nBesides its skill bonuses, Chromatic Ire also gives other bonuses that spellcasters would find useful, including a &lt;a href=\"Faster%20Cast%20Rate\"&gt;Faster Cast Rate&lt;/a&gt;. Its boost to &lt;a href=\"Resistances\"&gt;Resistances&lt;/a&gt; is useful in and &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;difficulties&lt;/a&gt;, and its rather large bonus to &lt;a href=\"life\"&gt;life&lt;/a&gt; is useful for any player. Although the damage it reflects on attackers is minimal, when surrounded, it distracts enemies long enough to allow for a Sorceress to cast an escape spell (e.g. ) or a crowd control spell (e.g. or ). \nStats.\nTwo-Hand Damage: 11 to 32\nRequired Level: 35\nRequired Strength: 25\nDurability: 35\nStaff class - "}
