{"id": "7768", "revid": "865253", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7768", "title": "Civerb's Cudgel", "text": "Civerb's Cudgel may refer to:"}
{"id": "7821", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7821", "title": "Civerb's Cudgel (Diablo I)", "text": "Civerb's Cudgel is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Maces\"&gt;Mace&lt;/a&gt; found in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\". Even though it doesn't look like a very good &lt;a href=\"Items\"&gt;item&lt;/a&gt;, mainly because of its drawbacks and also its low base damage, it still has a major advantage nonetheless: the +% Damage vs Demons applies to the total damage of the character(s), not just to the weapon's damage, effectively tripling the damage they deal to Demons in melee. Furthermore, Civerb's Cudgel is useful to &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s against &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s on Hell &lt;a href=\"difficulty\"&gt;difficulty&lt;/a&gt; which are &lt;a href=\"Immunity\"&gt;immune&lt;/a&gt; to their &lt;a href=\"Spellbook\"&gt;spells&lt;/a&gt;, and also since most of the monsters encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; levels are going to be Demons anyway. However it should be noted that Sorcerers are highly adviced to go with a more viable weapon choice, due to their insuffient &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Rating\"&gt;Chance To Hit&lt;/a&gt;, a much needed bonus that Civerb's Cudgel lacks, and slow &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt;, which is another important modifier needed on &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, in order to reach higher breakpoints."}
{"id": "4363", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4363", "title": "Civerb's Cudgel (Diablo II)", "text": "Civerb's Cudgel is a &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;set&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Scepter\"&gt;grand scepter&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". It is one of the three pieces of the &lt;a href=\"Civerb%27s%20Vestments\"&gt;Civerb's Vestments&lt;/a&gt; item set.\nCiverb's Cudgel is actually one of the most powerful early-game one-handed weapons, in terms of raw damage per hit. Most normal uniques can provide other helpful bonus, however.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: \nRequired Level: 9\nRequired Strength: 37\nDurability: 60\nBase Weapon Speed: [10]\n (varies)"}
