{"id": "48626", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48626", "title": "Claeys", "text": "Claeys was a &lt;a href=\"Crusader%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;crusader&lt;/a&gt;, and mentor to &lt;a href=\"Claeys%20%28Eudoxie%29\"&gt;Claeys&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nClaeys was the mentor to &lt;a href=\"Claeys%20%28Eudoxie%29\"&gt;Claeys&lt;/a&gt; (then known as Eudoxie), who he trained for years. At a point, he was led by his Inner Light to go to &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt; and serve at &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Prison\"&gt;its prison&lt;/a&gt;. Unfortunately, his student disagreed with his decision. This dispute eventually saw to them going their separate ways. At the prison, Claeys treated the prisoners fairly, and made sure other guards did the same. He also did his best to purge evil wherever he could find it at the island.He presumably died in defense of the island from the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nClaeys is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". His echo is featured in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Vowed%20to%20the%20Light\"&gt;Vowed to the Light&lt;/a&gt;\". In battle, he uses &lt;a href=\"Punish%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Punish&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Glare%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Shield Glare&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Conjuration%20of%20Light\"&gt;Conjuration of Light&lt;/a&gt; skills."}
{"id": "48621", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48621", "title": "Claeys (Eudoxie)", "text": "Claeys (formerly known as Eudoxie) is a &lt;a href=\"crusader\"&gt;crusader&lt;/a&gt;, vowed to purging &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt; of evil.\nBiography.\nEudoxie trained for years under &lt;a href=\"Claeys\"&gt;Claeys&lt;/a&gt; to learn the ways of a crusader. At a point, Claeys told that his inner &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; was leading him to serve at &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Prison\"&gt;Stormpoint's prison&lt;/a&gt;. However, she didn't agree with his decision, saying that serving at a prison would not contribute in cleansing the reputation of &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;their faith&lt;/a&gt;. After a short disagreement, he left for Stormpoint and told her not to follow. Some time later, she heard news that Claeys had died.\nAs per the traditions of the &lt;a href=\"crusaders\"&gt;crusaders&lt;/a&gt;, she was to take up her master's armor, his name and mission. She was still hesitant about that as Claeys' mission would see her stay in &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt;. Instead, she decided to seek counsel with the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; at the site of Claeys' death.\nOn her way, she met an &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt; who she requested for them to accompany her. After she performed a rite at Claeys' gravesite, an echo of the crusader was summoned.\nFinal Test.\nThe echo gave Eudoxie a chance for them to settle their dispute. After voicing her grievances, the echo justified himself, saying that he went to such dire place because it would give him the opportunity to do the most good, and that he treated the prisoners fairly, and made sure the other guards did the same. He then told Eudoxie to retrieve his shield from nearby. After Eudoxie retrieved the shield, (which had to be cleansed of the darkness that had infested it), her mentor's echo gave her a final test \u2014 to defeat him; because having faith demanded that she believed in herself, not others. After a long battle, Eudoxie was victorious.\nWith her trial complete, Claeys bestowed his armaments, his name, and his mission to purge Stormpoint of evil to his student. The newly christened Claeys took up her duty.\nIn-game.\nClaeys is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". She gives the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20Side%20Quests\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Vowed%20to%20the%20Light\"&gt;Vowed to the Light&lt;/a&gt;\". When in combat, she uses &lt;a href=\"Punish%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Punish&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shield%20Glare%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Shield Glare&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Conjuration%20of%20Light\"&gt;Conjuration of Light&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "44617", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44617", "title": "Claimer's Hollow", "text": "The is a &lt;a href=\"Helliquary\"&gt;Helliquary&lt;/a&gt; zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Located in &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;, it is here that players face &lt;a href=\"Gorgothra%20the%20Claimer\"&gt;Gorgothra&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe was removed as part of the &lt;a href=\"Unending%20Storm\"&gt;Unending Storm&lt;/a&gt; update, but was readded in the August 7 2024 update."}
{"id": "62", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=62", "title": "Clan", "text": "Clans are a gameplay feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". A clan can hold up to 100 players. A clan can become &lt;a href=\"Shadows\"&gt;Shadows&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Immortals\"&gt;Immortals&lt;/a&gt; as a whole. Clans can own &lt;a href=\"Accursed%20Towers\"&gt;Accursed Towers&lt;/a&gt;.\nClan names can be changed for 1,500 &lt;a href=\"Platinum\"&gt;Platinum&lt;/a&gt;, with a cooldown of 7 days.\nHistory.\nThe name change feature was introduced in the update.\nIn the update, a clan roster feature was added to allow leaders/officers to view personnel changes."}
{"id": "1904", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1904", "title": "Clan Skeld", "text": "Clan Skeld is a &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; clan.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Uileloscadh%20M%C3%B3r\"&gt;Uileloscadh M\u00f3r&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt; came under attack by &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;forces&lt;/a&gt;. The clan dispatched its &lt;a href=\"warrior\"&gt;warrior&lt;/a&gt;s on an offensive, but this left the clan's village only lightly defended, with just a handful of guards. The village came under attack by &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, and the guards could do little to stem their advance. However, the village and clan were saved by the Druid &lt;a href=\"Azgar\"&gt;Azgar&lt;/a&gt;, albeit at the cost of his own life."}
{"id": "2980", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2980", "title": "Clan of the Seven Stones", "text": "The Clan of the Seven Stones is an &lt;a href=\"Umbaru\"&gt;Umbaru&lt;/a&gt; tribe. Their cultural folklore is related to seven sacred stones; one of which is the &lt;a href=\"Iceburn%20Tear\"&gt;Iceburn Tear&lt;/a&gt;. Members of this tribe regularly go on pilgrims in search of any of the &lt;a href=\"Seven%20Stones\"&gt;Seven Stones&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe frequently engages in tribal warfare with the tribes of the &lt;a href=\"Tribe%20of%20the%20Clouded%20Valley\"&gt;Clouded Valley&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tribe%20of%20the%20Five%20Hills\"&gt;Five Hills&lt;/a&gt; so that they may replenish their supply of raw materials for the human sacrifices that their civilization revolves around.\nLike the rest of the Umbaru, the Clan of the Seven Stones is in a period of social upheaval due to an incident concerning their most current war."}
