{"id": "52159", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52159", "title": "Fell Council", "text": "The Fell Council is a quintet of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s. \nLore.\nThe Fell Council is composed of former members of the &lt;a href=\"High%20Council%20of%20Zakarum\"&gt;High Council of Zakarum&lt;/a&gt;. Once faithful and generous leaders of their people, they were enthralled by &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;, and abused their positions to corrupt the &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; from within, and misguide the faithful into attacking those who follow the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt;. Mephisto rewarded them for their service by turning them into demons and granting them abilities far beyond &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;mortals&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, the Fell Council was based in the &lt;a href=\"Well%20of%20Hatred\"&gt;Well of Hatred&lt;/a&gt;. They were confronted by .\nIn-game.\nThe Fell Council are enemies in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", introduced in &lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20the%20Infernal%20Hordes\"&gt;Season of the Infernal Hordes&lt;/a&gt;. They are found at the end of the &lt;a href=\"Infernal%20Hordes\"&gt;Infernal Hordes&lt;/a&gt; gameplay mode.\nThere are 5 Fell Council Members in total, each equipped with different unique abilities. Every time a player faces the Council, there will be 3 different members to fight, selected at random. Once enough damage is inflicted on the council, the priests will become more frenzied in their attacks. Once the Council is defeated, players can spend their &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Aether\"&gt;Burning Aether&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Spoils%20of%20Hell\"&gt;Spoils of Hell&lt;/a&gt;."}
