{"id": "47168", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47168", "title": "Fernam", "text": "Fernam was the founder of the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Knights\"&gt;Blood Knights&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nCenturies before the destruction of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, Fernam was a soldier assigned to protect a lord in &lt;a href=\"Gea%20Kul\"&gt;Gea Kul&lt;/a&gt;, who was was infatuated with &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt;s and their immortality. One day, a vampire imprisoned in the lord's keep broke free, killed the lord, and gravely wounded Fernam during the escape, infecting him with vampirism. Fortunately, the lord's top &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;\u2014a premier scholar on the subject of vampirism\u2014had performed a ritual on Fernam to stop the spread before he was transformed into a feral, mindless thrall. The Mage was successful in keeping him alive, but instead of granting immortality, Fernam unexpectedly inherited some of the vampire\u2019s power.\nThe Mage had been mortally wounded in the scuffle, and with his dying breath, taught Fernam how to perform the ritual that saved his life. At any moment, Fernam could succumb to his newfound darkness and transform indefinitely into a vampiric thrall. After cheating fate, Fernam took his lord's wealth and moved into the catacombs below the keep. He formed the order of Blood Knights, used the catacombs as a training ground, and passed on knowledge of the curse-suspending ritual that saved his life along with the way of his preferred weapon, the polearm.\nAt a point, Fernam made &lt;a href=\"Heir%20of%20High%20Regions\"&gt;a helm&lt;/a&gt; to symbolize his war against the darkness.\nLegacy.\nFernam later disappeared, and was replaced by a Blood Knight council. All Blood Knights take the same oath Fernam made\u2014\"all that remains of my life, weighed against the darkness.\"\nBefore he left, Fernam entrusted his &lt;a href=\"Fernam%27s%20Birthmantle\"&gt;birthmantle&lt;/a&gt;, stained with the blood of dozens of vampires, to his order. The mantle became a treasured artefact, and it was an affront for it to be worn outside a chapterhouse.\nAfter Fernam vanished, he was accused of vagrancy for not assisting his order. Replicas of his original helm were made, which saved enough Blood Knights from decapitation that it has acquired its own legendry status, and led to murmurs of the first knight watching over the chapterhouse still. \nTwo relics of Fernam are known to survive; the &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20Fernam\"&gt;Crown of Fernam&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Fang%20of%20Fernam\"&gt;Fang of Fernam&lt;/a&gt;. Taken together, the two artifacts represent the duality that exists within all Blood Knights."}
