{"id": "8338", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=8338", "title": "Festering Appendage", "text": "Festering Appendages are a type of summoned monster that are associated with &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;, the Lord of Destruction. \nIn game.\nDiablo II.\nFestering Appendages appear as tendrils which spring from the ground to attack players. Each appendage has three fingers that can strike at players as they run towards Baal. Baal summons them during the final confrontation within &lt;a href=\"The%20Worldstone%20Chamber\"&gt;The Worldstone Chamber&lt;/a&gt;. They will disappear after a set amount of time, but are usually hard to kill since they quickly vanish into the ground, though at times, they \"can\" be shattered using cold attacks such as &lt;a href=\"Hurricane\"&gt;Hurricane&lt;/a&gt;. Contrary to popular belief, they do not firmly root to the ground and players can &lt;a href=\"knockback\"&gt;knockback&lt;/a&gt; them.\nThere are five variations of them, and &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt; spawns two different types depending on difficulty. The fifth variation is unused.\nDiablo Immortal.\nFestering Appendages appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are briefly encountered in &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt;'s workshop, and are summoned by Baal in his boss confrontation. They function nearly identical to their form in \"Lord of Destruction\", but persist until they are destroyed.\n are also encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Domain%20of%20Horror\"&gt;Domain of Horror&lt;/a&gt; during \"&lt;a href=\"Stranger%20in%20the%20Sands\"&gt;Stranger in the Sands&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"elite%20quest\"&gt;elite quest&lt;/a&gt;."}
