{"id": "41588", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41588", "title": "Fetid Swamp", "text": "The Fetid Swamp is a marsh in the center of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt; zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nIn the Fetid Swamp, light doesn't reach the floor, and dense fog permeates the air above the dark water. Dangerous creatures dwell in the Fetid Swamp, and they drag unwitting victims to their death.\nAfter the defeat of &lt;a href=\"the%20Countess\"&gt;the Countess&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Sisterhood%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisterhood of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt; made efforts to cleanse the swamp of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s. To this end, they requested aid from adventurers in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe Fetid Swamp is a &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wood\"&gt;Dark Wood&lt;/a&gt; zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "2657", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2657", "title": "Fetish", "text": "The Fetish are a group of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s found primarily in the jungles around &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Fetish were created centuries ago at the hands of an unknown demon or &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;. Attacking with enormous, vicious knives or at range with deadly blow darts, the Fetish are native inhabitants to the jungles that surround Kurast. Known cannibals, they are small, intelligent beings in league with the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;forces&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;, though will often serve evil &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt;s and tribal Sorcerers. They stalk their prey, rushing to the attack from hiding and slashing with jagged hunting knives. Individually, Fetishes are weak and easy to kill. However, they are much more formidable when attacking en masse; if one Fetish is slain, the rest dash to cover at high speed to attack with their blow guns and then hide. Once hidden, they stop and begin to stalk their foes again. \nWhen accompanied by a &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20Shaman\"&gt;Shaman&lt;/a&gt;, they are doubly dangerous, as their Shaman possess the ability to revive their fallen kin.\nFetishes are also found on &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt;. By &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, the Fetishes had become increasingly bold, directly attacking Bilefen's &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; settlements. These Fetishes carry &lt;a href=\"bone%20ormanet\"&gt;bone ormanet&lt;/a&gt;s.\nTypes.\nFetish can be organized into the following sub-types:\nIn-game.\nDiablo Immortal.\nFetish are encountered as enemies on &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are encountered in the &lt;a href=\"Kikuras%20Rapids\"&gt;Kikuras Rapids&lt;/a&gt; dungeon, attacking from both range and in melee.\nDiablo III.\nFetish appear in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" via the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20Army\"&gt;Fetish Army&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nDiablo IV.\nFetish appear as enemies in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\" in &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "40671", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40671", "title": "Fetish11", "text": "This Rat Man is an special &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Fetish&lt;/a&gt; type. He spawns as random &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Flayer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20Blowdart%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Flayer Blowdart&lt;/a&gt; minions upon activating an altar in &lt;a href=\"Flayer%20Jungle\"&gt;Flayer Jungle&lt;/a&gt; ruins, while doing the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Old%20Religion%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Blade of Old Religion&lt;/a&gt; quest. The Unique Rat Man drops &lt;a href=\"The%20Gidbinn%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;The Gidbinn&lt;/a&gt;. While it's a random &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt;, this monster is more than that by being a special quest variation of &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Fetish&lt;/a&gt;.\nWeirdly there are no &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Fetish&lt;/a&gt; codenamed fetish9 and fetish10.\nStatistics.\nDevelopment.\nOriginally in v1.00 the minions of this Fetish variant were the same variant."}
