{"id": "40480", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40480", "title": "Fetish (Diablo II)", "text": "Fetish are a type of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nFetish are weak individually, but pose degree of danger when in numbers. Like the &lt;a href=\"Fallen\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt;, Fetish are easily dispatched mostly with one or two blows. However, they provide an unbelievably great nuisance as they are extremely fast on foot and attack in large numbers. Due to this reason, cold magic or area-of-effect magic are advised against them.\nIn &lt;a href=\"The%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt;, players can encounter only the melee variation of the Fetish known as the Rat Man, the lowest variant of the &lt;a href=\"Fetish\"&gt;Fetish&lt;/a&gt;, in the first level of the &lt;a href=\"Catacombs\"&gt;Catacombs&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Monastery\"&gt;Rogue Monastery&lt;/a&gt;. Other variations are encountered in &lt;a href=\"The%20Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; and known as Flayer, Soul Killer and Stygian Doll. There is a special random &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fetish11\"&gt;Rat Man&lt;/a&gt; spawning in the &lt;a href=\"Blade%20of%20the%20Old%20Religion%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Blade of Old Religion&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;.\nDevelopment.\nA Pre-release Necromancer showcase video from 1999 December 15 shows Rat Men appearing as minions (of a presumably &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; Rat Man) in &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Forest\"&gt;Spider Forest&lt;/a&gt;."}
