{"id": "2658", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2658", "title": "Fetish Shaman", "text": "The Fetish Shaman is a type of &lt;a href=\"Fetish\"&gt;Fetish&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nFetish Shamans are marked by their elaborate headdresses. They are capable of creating additional Fetish, and lead them into wars of their own devising. The Shamans are always borne upon the shoulders of a lesser Fetish. Undoubtedly, they believe that this appearance of added height makes them look more ferocious and is befitting their station. Their ability to resurrect their dead and breathe great gouts of flame ensures that none of their brethren will argue with their \"lofty\" requirements.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nFetish Shaman are monsters found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" in the jungles. They are the higher-level equivalent of &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Fallen%20Shaman\"&gt;Fallen Shaman&lt;/a&gt;. They are chosen from the most intelligent &lt;a href=\"Fetish\"&gt;Fetish&lt;/a&gt; of a tribe. They aid their kin by having the ability to breathe fire and revive their slain kin.\nKill the Fetish Shaman first because they can resurrect other &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Fetishes&lt;/a&gt;. Beware of their highly damaging &lt;a href=\"Inferno%20%28monster%20skill%29\"&gt;Inferno&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; attacks. Having &lt;a href=\"resistance\"&gt;resistance&lt;/a&gt; to Fire is useful. If you kill Shaman, the normal 'carrier' fetish will be released and attack you. He can no longer use fire spells or resurrect other Fetish. Note that if you kill &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique\"&gt;Super Unique&lt;/a&gt; Shaman, the carrier will also be a Super Unique but with little health (and often with the same name). You get unique loot from both the killing the shamans and then from killing the carrier. They use resurrect rarely, because it's melee-range and they like to wander in random directions, their real threat is their inferno attack and a big number of fast fetishes.\nFetish Shaman come in five variants: Ratman Shaman, Flayer Shaman, Flayer Shaman, Soul Killer Shaman, and Stygian Doll Shaman\nStats.\nNote: Damage 1 refers to the damage done by their Inferno attack.\nFetish Shamans use the following Skills: , .\nDiablo Immortal.\nFetish Shamans reappear as enemies in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" on &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt;. They retain their ability to breathe fire, as well as lobbing and shooting fireballs."}
