{"id": "28728", "revid": "5562046", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28728", "title": "Fezuul", "text": "Fezuul, Master of Bone,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He spawns for an unmarked event.\nIn their journey, players may find a strange pond filled with dried bones. If these bones are touched, multiple &lt;a href=\"Skeleton\"&gt;Skeleton&lt;/a&gt;s along with Fezuul himself will appear, commanding his minions to kill &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; and drink his or her blood.\nIn combat, he has no affixes, but summons more and more Skeletons until killed.\nUpon death, he drops the &lt;a href=\"Tomes\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"The%20Promises%20of%20Fezuul%20al-Kazaar\"&gt;The Promises of Fezuul al-Kazaar&lt;/a&gt;, which reveals that Fezuul al-Kazaar lured his followers into the desert, promising them transformation beyond recognition. This promise was kept, however: all of his followers were turned to &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "33364", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33364", "title": "Fharzula", "text": "Fharzula, Imperial Executioner,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Colossal%20Golgor\"&gt;Colossal Golgor&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Tower%20Study\"&gt;Ancient Tower Study&lt;/a&gt; above the &lt;a href=\"Greyhollow%20Island\"&gt;Greyhollow Island&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It's the only Colossal Golgor in Act V, and has slightly different appearance. He can be nominated a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn combat, he has a Vortex affix, as well as greatly empowered &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; and damage. To his advantage, the area is \"very\" small, with little to no space for maneuvering.\nFharzula is summoned by the spirit of &lt;a href=\"High%20Cleric\"&gt;High Cleric&lt;/a&gt; for an unmarked event, when player touches his tome. Killing him opens the way to &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Tower%20Battlements\"&gt;Ancient Tower Battlements&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "33351", "revid": "5134523", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33351", "title": "Fharzula (Tome)", "text": "Fharzula is a &lt;a href=\"tome\"&gt;tome&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" in on &lt;a href=\"Greyhollow%20Island\"&gt;Greyhollow Island&lt;/a&gt;. It is written by the &lt;a href=\"High%20Cleric\"&gt;High Cleric&lt;/a&gt;, and drops when &lt;a href=\"Fharzula\"&gt;Fharzula&lt;/a&gt; is slain in the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Tower%20Study\"&gt;Ancient Tower Study&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt reads as follows:\n\"Awaken. Obey. Sacrifice.\""}
