{"id": "40802", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40802", "title": "Fields of Hatred", "text": "Fields of Hatred are a &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; feature of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe Fields of Hatred are areas in Sanctuary that have been tainted by the hatred of &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;, which bubbled up from Hell. Those who entered these fields were consumed, turning them against their fellow &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;mortal&lt;/a&gt;s. Numerous &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s flock to these areas of their own volition, looking to claim renown through &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; and zeal.\nGameplay.\nThe Fields are found in the open-world. Players can enter these areas at will, where they will be able to engage in PvP against other players. Players can collect &lt;a href=\"Shard%20of%20Hatred%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;Shards of Hatred&lt;/a&gt; in these zones, from defeating enemy players, as well as killing &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s in the zone. Special vendors are found in the Fields where players can spend their shards.\nAs a player kills other players and collects shards, they slowly infuse themselves with the Curse of Mephisto. Do this enough, and they become a Vessel of Hatred. When this occurs, everyone within a large radius will be made aware of the player on their map. Killing a Vessel of Hatred gives a bonus. If the Vessel stays alive within the area, they get a large bonus at the end of the event.\nThrough killing monsters in the zone, players can collect &lt;a href=\"Seed%20of%20Hatred\"&gt;Seeds of Hatred&lt;/a&gt;. To make use of the seeds, players need to bring them to the Altar of Extraction where they can be smashed into &lt;a href=\"Red%20Dust\"&gt;Red Dust&lt;/a&gt;. If players are killed in the zone, the seeds are dropped. Red Dust, however, is not lost.\nFields of Hatred will have leaderboards and other gameplay incentives."}
