{"id": "3180", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3180", "title": "Finger Mage", "text": "Finger Mages were created during the &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Wars\"&gt;Mage Wars&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Sorcerer\"&gt;Sorcerer&lt;/a&gt;s used these creatures to defeat rival sorcerers, reasoning that an enemy spellcaster weakened by taking away all of his &lt;a href=\"mana\"&gt;mana&lt;/a&gt;. When the Mage Wars were over, Finger Mages were abandoned and left to die. Many of these creatures are found in Hell because they seek great sources of energy there. These &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; monstrosities have the ability to fire homing \"missiles\" that drain the mana of its target. In addition, they possess the ability to stun whatever they attack.\nMostly they appear in Act IV in the City of the Damned, the River of Flame and the Chaos Sanctuary.\nFinger Mages have three variants:\nOn &lt;a href=\"Hell%20difficulty\"&gt;Hell difficulty&lt;/a&gt;, all variants of the Finger Mage are immune to . Also all variants have a resistance to &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Normal%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Normal&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;, but lose it in Hell.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Grand%20Vizier%20of%20Chaos\"&gt;Grand Vizier of Chaos&lt;/a&gt; is a super unique Finger Mage and also one of &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;'s three elite guards.\nNotes.\nAt first their mana drain missiles look like an red lightning bolt, but upon close glance they are revealed to be glowing Spiders made of energy. "}
