{"id": "1638", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1638", "title": "Fire Arrow", "text": "Fire Arrow is an &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"&lt;a href=\"Hefaetrus\"&gt;Hefaetrus&lt;/a&gt; is the &lt;a href=\"Amazonian\"&gt;Amazonian&lt;/a&gt; god of &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; and rebirth who lives deep within the great volcano, &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Arnazeus\"&gt;Mount Arnazeus&lt;/a&gt;, on the island of &lt;a href=\"Philios\"&gt;Philios&lt;/a&gt;. Although primarily the patron deity of farmers, from time to time he bestows his favors upon the warriors of the Islands, so they may keep safe his congregation. Through proper prayer and the sacrifice of many fierce enemies, an especially brave Amazon can attain the power to imbue her shots with the destructive power of fire, allowing her to rake blazing missiles from her bow. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nThis skill adds fire damage to arrows fired by the user.\u00a0It also converts part of the physical damage from the arrow itself into fire damage, which may be useful for getting past enemies immune to physical damage. However,\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Magic%20Arrow\"&gt;Magic Arrow&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0is generally better for that purpose, as magic resistance is rare even in Hell, and the ability to not use up arrows can be useful in such a case (where many arrows may need to be expended to kill the enemies in question), as Fire Arrow actually\u00a0\"does\"\u00a0consume an arrow when fired. Fire Arrow is useful in early parts of the game, but is less effective than\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Exploding%20Arrow\"&gt;Exploding Arrow&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Immolation%20Arrow\"&gt;Immolation Arrow&lt;/a&gt; available at higher levels.\u00a0\nSome\u00a0&lt;a href=\"The%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Rogue%20Archer\"&gt;Rogue Archer&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Hireling\"&gt;Hireling&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0use this skill."}
