{"id": "4898", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4898", "title": "Fire Claws", "text": "Fire Claws is a &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nSynergies.\nUsage.\nUnlike other similar skills, Fire Claws may be used in \"both\" &lt;a href=\"Werewolf\"&gt;Werewolf&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Werebear\"&gt;Werebear&lt;/a&gt; form.\nThis allows the druid to get through some &lt;a href=\"Immune%20to%20Physical\"&gt;Immune to Physical&lt;/a&gt; creatures by dealing a bit of &lt;a href=\"fire%20damage\"&gt;fire damage&lt;/a&gt;. Though the number may not look great, the synergies really put a huge bump in the damage. Maxing any one of them gives you +440% damage, making the level 20 skill hit for roughly 2500 fire damage; maxing all the synergies gives you roughly 4.5k fire damage.\nIt is one of the few skills in game that gain &lt;a href=\"synergies\"&gt;synergies&lt;/a&gt; from skills of \"another\" &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Tree\"&gt;Skill Tree&lt;/a&gt;. Even though most &lt;a href=\"Elemental%20Skills\"&gt;Elemental Skills&lt;/a&gt; cannot be cast in beast form, the real usefulness of this effect is immense.\nLore.\n\"While in his animal form, a Druid can use his affinity with the natural elements in order to supplement his attacks with a blazing assault. \"\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 4"}
