{"id": "47515", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47515", "title": "Fire of Life", "text": "The Fire of Life is the union of &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt;' and &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"essence\"&gt;essence&lt;/a&gt; (called the Father's and Mother's Legacy by the locals) that they imbued into &lt;a href=\"Ancients%27%20Cradle\"&gt;Ancients' Cradle&lt;/a&gt;. It flows freely through the island in the appearance of a faint lavender aura.\nLore.\nThe is a powerful force that permeates everywhere on the Ancients' Cradle. In high concentrations the condenses into crystals (a property originating from the Mother's Legacy). The locals use it to substitute for &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Power\"&gt;Arcane Power&lt;/a&gt;, and perform &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; by drawing it from the land, or from different structures brimming with it. In dire times when no suitable sources are near, an Inari or Lilin can draw the from their own &lt;a href=\"life\"&gt;life&lt;/a&gt; force. Because of its constituent nature, spells cast from unbalanced source of the are weaker than spells cast using only one of its components. It is also used to power the different defensive structures of the land. To best channel the , the &lt;a href=\"Pathstone\"&gt;Pathstone&lt;/a&gt; is needed. \nThe is made up of the Father's Legacy and the Mother's Legacy in a balanced union. &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;ic energies can unbalance it, though the Father's Legacy tries to resist it. When unbalanced, the Mother's Legacy goes rampant and begins to corrupt everything, including &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;animal&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Sacred%20Guardian\"&gt;constructs&lt;/a&gt;, the environment, and even the dead.\nFather's Legacy.\nThe Father's Legacy is the &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;ic half of the . It is the essence of Inarius, and originates from his shrine at the western end of the island. It has the appearance of a glorious golden aura, and has been likened to a &lt;a href=\"deities\"&gt;god&lt;/a&gt;.\nAll structures in &lt;a href=\"Shieldholm\"&gt;Shieldholm&lt;/a&gt; are powered by the Father's Legacy. &lt;a href=\"Inari\"&gt;Inari&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Conservator\"&gt;Conservator&lt;/a&gt;s wield staves that enable them to channel the Father's Legacy exclusively for various effects like &lt;a href=\"teleport\"&gt;teleport&lt;/a&gt;ing, creating barriers and binding prisoners. The Father's Legacy is used to enact sentences such as &lt;a href=\"Purity%27s%20Penance\"&gt;Purity's Penance&lt;/a&gt;; a punishment where the condemned is bound by Conservators and is made to endure several lightning strikes of the Father's Legacy. The extent of injury the condemned receives depends on the guilt \u2014 from unscathed (completely innocent) to blindness, to &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt; (severe guilt).\nMother's Legacy.\nThe Mother's Legacy is the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic half of the . It is the essence of Lilith, and originates from her shrine at the northern end of the island. It has the appearance of a ominous red aura. Because of its nature, it can easily be used by cultists for demonic magic, and in large concentrations, can even overpower its counterpart.\nThe Mother's Legacy is very corrupting, and is the main cause of the affliction. &lt;a href=\"The%20Afflicted\"&gt;The Afflicted&lt;/a&gt; have been observed to only be able to channel it, and not the full .\nDespite this, the Lilin normally imbue their weapons with the Mother's Legacy.\nHistory.\nThe Beginning.\nAfter Inarius banished Lilith to the &lt;a href=\"Void\"&gt;Void&lt;/a&gt;, he returned to Ancients' Cradle changed. He condemned the &lt;a href=\"Lilin\"&gt;Lilin&lt;/a&gt; for siding with Lilith and took the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; from the island. He also sealed the to embers. Before he left, he created the &lt;a href=\"Pathstone\"&gt;Pathstone&lt;/a&gt; from the that would keep it stable. He then gave the artifact to one of &lt;a href=\"Inari\"&gt;his favored&lt;/a&gt; (the first &lt;a href=\"Prevailing%20Wind\"&gt;Prevailing Wind&lt;/a&gt;).\nWithout Inarius or Lilith, the was maintained by embers drawn from the shrines to Inarius and Lilith at &lt;a href=\"Shieldholm\"&gt;Shieldholm&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Commingling%20Pit\"&gt;Commingling Pit&lt;/a&gt;.\nRampancy.\nOver time, the Inari gradually seized power for themselves and began to suppress the Lilin. At a point in the 13th century, Elder &lt;a href=\"Morwith\"&gt;Morwith&lt;/a&gt; of the Lilin stole the Pathstone (the only way in or out of the Cradle) and escaped with her followers.\nWithout the Pathstone to stabilize it, the tilted towards Lilith's Legacy (likely because of the hatred existing between the Inari and Lilin), and began to run rampant across the island. This caused social breakdown of both the &lt;a href=\"Inari\"&gt;Inari&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Lilin\"&gt;Lilin&lt;/a&gt;, and disfigured everything it touched. &lt;a href=\"Animals\"&gt;Animals&lt;/a&gt; and plants were fused together to form &lt;a href=\"Amalgamations\"&gt;new monstrosities&lt;/a&gt;.\nSome of the Lilin, desperate to cure themselves of the affliction, began offering sacrifices to Lilith and begging for her favor at her shrine in the Commingling Pit.\nIt Began with Terror....\nC. &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt; arrived at the Ancients' Cradle.\nThey tried drawing on the through one of the obelisks scattered around on the &lt;a href=\"Hinderlands\"&gt;outskirts of the island&lt;/a&gt;, but was rejected by the Father's Legacy. After that, they traveled deeper into the island, torturing and questioning the locals but were unable to get information. Instead they managed to rouse the fury of the .\nThe cult were able to harvest some of the Mother's Legacy successfully"}
