{"id": "16012", "revid": "154566", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16012", "title": "Fireball (monster skill)", "text": "Fireballs are a monster skill not unlike the &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt; skill of the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Ball\"&gt;same name&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey are &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; attacks that fly through the air for a short distance until colliding with an object or spontaneously exploding at their maximum range. The explosion causes area of effect damage, making the projectile more difficult to dodge.\n&lt;a href=\"Vampire\"&gt;Vampire&lt;/a&gt;s cast both Fireballs and similar-looking &lt;a href=\"Leech-life%20Ball\"&gt;Leech-life Ball&lt;/a&gt;s. The Fireball is a sphere of fire and does not absorb life, whereas the Life Steal Missile resembles a burning skull and causes the red life-stealing vortex to appear over the Vampire on a successful hit. "}
{"id": "37669", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37669", "title": "Firebat", "text": "The Firebat is an &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic &lt;a href=\"Animals\"&gt;animal&lt;/a&gt; monster that looks like a mixture between a &lt;a href=\"Winged%20Fiend\"&gt;Winged Fiend&lt;/a&gt; head and the hovering body of a &lt;a href=\"Gargoyle\"&gt;Gargoyle&lt;/a&gt;. It appears in &lt;a href=\"Crypt\"&gt;Crypt&lt;/a&gt; level 1-2.\nThese blood red colored,\u00a0flapping, hopping, bloated bat-like things are fire-based ranged attackers blessed with one of the most annoying squeals heard in all of Hellfire (which is really saying something) that attacks the characters encountered by shooting &lt;a href=\"Firebolt\"&gt;Firebolt&lt;/a&gt;s. They also boast a very annoying AI; they're too stupid to get around corners or through doorways very well, so it's difficult to lure them into a closed area, and corner traps of the type that work on most archers and Succubi are useless against them. The best tactic is to reduce them to meaty chunks using or . Fortunately, they're very slow as the hop along, flapping their vestigial wings, and can be run down fairly easily by melee characters."}
{"id": "9166", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9166", "title": "Firebats", "text": "Firebats\u00a0is a Fire spell used by\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt;s\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nChannels a swarm of fiery bats, hitting all enemies in a 20 yard, 45 degree cone in front of the Witch Doctor for &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage per tick. This counts as a torrent, bypassing most obstacles (including &lt;a href=\"Waller\"&gt;Waller&lt;/a&gt; barriers), only stopping if it hits a solid wall."}
