{"id": "52881", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52881", "title": "First Khazra", "text": "The First Khazra are &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; who reside in the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Citadel\"&gt;Dark Citadel&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nThe First Khazra are malignant beings and use &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; extensively. They are the descendants of the khazra who remained in the citadel while other khazra spread across &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. As such, they are a throwback to the khazra's original forms. They used the powers within the citadel and the crater it was located in to perform experiments in order to bring back their &lt;a href=\"Zagraal\"&gt;dark god&lt;/a&gt;. They used the &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt;s of &lt;a href=\"Mage\"&gt;Mage&lt;/a&gt;s that lingered in the crater surrounding the Citadel to power their experiments.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Enmity\"&gt;Great Enmity&lt;/a&gt;, the khazra began abducting &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;s who strayed into their territory, and even abducted their own kind, using both to power their experiments. By &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, their plan to resurrect Zagraal, their patron deity was nearing fruition. No longer content to stay inside the citadel, the First Khazra began raiding &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;, attacking in the night and abducting people to bring back to the citadel. Numerous heroes tried to do something about the First Khazra, but all of them failed.\nIn-game.\nThe First Khazra are found inside the Dark Citadel in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". They are one of the game's &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; families."}
