{"id": "2668", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2668", "title": "Firstborn", "text": "The Firstborn, otherwise referred to as the Ancients or Old Gods were the first generation of &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nThe Firstborn were created from the union of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;, and in turn, gave birth to nephalem. &lt;a href=\"Linarian\"&gt;Linarian&lt;/a&gt; was the first nephalem to come into being.\nIn their early days, such was their ignorance of &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;, the Firstborn did not have burial rites, as they had never had to deal with the &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt; of their own. Not even &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt;s or &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s could give their offspring the immortality they themselves enjoyed. \nThe cultures the Firstborn fostered developed along very different lines. None of these cultures had writing involved at the time. &lt;a href=\"Akarat\"&gt;Akarat&lt;/a&gt; believed (or at least claimed) that they embraced the &lt;a href=\"Light\"&gt;Light&lt;/a&gt; completely.\nFirstborn erected &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20Lilith\"&gt;altars&lt;/a&gt; in honor of &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt;. As they roamed Sanctuary, they rode upon the most powerful of steeds. They placed powerful runes upon their coats and dressed them in nature's armors.\nOnly a few of the Ancients survived &lt;a href=\"the%20Purge\"&gt;the Purge&lt;/a&gt;. Of those who remained, &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; sought to punish any who used their powers. In light of Inarius's tampering with the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, the nephalem diminished in power with each subsequent generation, eventually devolving into the mortal race known as &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt;ity. However, the Firstborn appeared to have fared better than their descendants, and it is said that the Firstborn retained their immortality. However, the Ancients' powers were still diminished by the Worldstone's dampening effect. One group of Ancients led by Lord &lt;a href=\"Zir\"&gt;Zir&lt;/a&gt; reacted violently to this change of condition, and for their actions, were imprisoned in the underground &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20the%20Ancients\"&gt;City of the Ancients&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is said that the Ancients took a guiding hand in the development of humanity before fading into myth. The &lt;a href=\"Oxen%20Tribe\"&gt;Oxen Tribe&lt;/a&gt; hold that weapons wielded by the fiercest &lt;a href=\"Warrior\"&gt;Warrior&lt;/a&gt;s often catch the eye of Ancient spirits. If the wielder is worthy, the spirits may bless the steel with their strength.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nThree Ancients, &lt;a href=\"Talic\"&gt;Talic the Defender&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Madawc\"&gt;Madawc the Guardian&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Korlic\"&gt;Korlic the Protector&lt;/a&gt;, are encountered on the &lt;a href=\"Arreat%20Summit\"&gt;Arreat Summit&lt;/a&gt; after consulting the &lt;a href=\"Altar%20of%20the%20Heavens\"&gt;Altar of the Heavens&lt;/a&gt;. They must be fought and defeated in order to complete the storyline of \"\". Heroes should be warned that the Ancients will reset if they use a &lt;a href=\"portal\"&gt;portal&lt;/a&gt; to return to Harrogath, and therefore, must be fully prepared for a long and dangerous clash.\nDiablo III.\nIf a &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt; uses the &lt;a href=\"Call%20of%20the%20Ancients\"&gt;Call of the Ancients&lt;/a&gt; skill, the Ancients that were fought in \"Lord of Destruction\" will temporarily lend their aid to the cause. This limited duration can be made permanent with the &lt;a href=\"Immortal%20King%27s%20Call\"&gt;Immortal King's Call&lt;/a&gt; set bonuses, although the Ancients can be killed."}
{"id": "52367", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52367", "title": "Fisher's Frenzy", "text": "Fisher's Frenzy is a \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" event that runs from July 10 to July 24, 2024, as part of the &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Solstice\"&gt;Cursed Solstice&lt;/a&gt; update.\nDuring the event, players travel to the &lt;a href=\"Shimmering%20Tropic\"&gt;Shimmering Tropic&lt;/a&gt; for &lt;a href=\"fishing\"&gt;fishing&lt;/a&gt;. Casting a line in the event gives players the chance to earn you a Lost Jade Fishing Rod, a mythical piece of unique angler gear from days of old. Players can compete amongst the leaderboard to see who can land the biggest fish. Completing tasks within the event earns players &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;Set Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt;, and more. Note that these rewards only apply to the Shimmering Tropic."}
{"id": "50880", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50880", "title": "Fishing", "text": "Fishing is a gameplay element in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is unlocked after completing \"&lt;a href=\"The%20Greatest%20Pastime\"&gt;The Greatest Pastime&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGameplay.\nAfter receiving the fishing rod, fishing can be done in &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Cemetery\"&gt;Ashwold Cemetery&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bilefen\"&gt;Bilefen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Tundra\"&gt;Frozen Tundra&lt;/a&gt;. These maps have a Fisher NPC that sells bait and exchanges any caught fish, and there are fishing spots next to them. However there are additional fishing spots on bridges and in some shore areas.\nAfter obtaining bait, the rod can be cast in a fishing area. A gauge appears at the top of the screen that is divided into 3 sections. The first section takes 1 minute to fill, the second one takes an additional 1 minute 30 seconds (2 minutes 30 seconds total) and the third one takes an additional 2 minutes 40 seconds (5 minutes 10 seconds total). Fish will randomly bite and can be reeled in or let go. Even if the fish is let go, the bait is used up. A bite will no longer disappear when the timer hits around 5 minutes. When reeling in a fish, a different gauge replaces the time gauge. A window randomly goes left or right on the gauge, and there is a marker that must be kept within the window. The marker normally moves left, and clicking moves it to the right. If the marker stays outside the window for too long, the fish gets away. The timer won't reset if the bite started before the 5 minute mark. The size of the window depends on the rarity of the fish, with rarer fish having smaller windows, which can be used as a clue if looking for a specific fish as any fish that is not the desired rarity can be let go to avoid restarting the timer.\nThe rarity of the fish depends on the section of the timer that was active during the bite: the first section results in a Common fish, the second one results in a Magic fish, and the third section results in a Rare or higher quality fish. If the bar moves to a different section while the bite is active, the fish will still be of the rarity corresponding to the section the bite started in.\nA player can carry up to 20 fish. Turning in fish rewards gold and equipment.\nThere is a small chance to fish up a chest that contains items and a &lt;a href=\"Normal%20Gems\"&gt;Normal Gem&lt;/a&gt;. This has a limit of 3 per day.\nList of fish.\n!Name\n!Rarity\n!colspan=\"3\"|Zones\n!Time range"}
