{"id": "3010", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3010", "title": "Fist of the Heavens (Diablo II)", "text": "Fist of the Heavens is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"This spell allows the Paladin to summon the power of holy vengeance. Manifesting as lightning from the heavens, these bolts rain down from the sky, exploding into a thousand shafts of light that radiate outwards to banish the evil from the battlefield. \"\nGeneral Information.\nWhen cast, Fist of the Heavens calls down a lightning bolt, hitting the targeted enemy for high Lightning damage.\nFrom the impact point, four Holy Bolts spread out around the area. These bolts are not duplicates of the respective skill, but instead are resolved independently (though they highly synergize with the aforementioned skill). Also unlike normal Holy Bolts, Bolts created through Fist of the Heavens provide no healing to allies.\nThis skill is primarily useful against large collections of Undead and Demonic foes, but also can be used against other monsters for the direct Lightning damage. Fist of the Heavens always hits, and ignores most obstacles in its way.\nFist of the Heavens pairs best with the &lt;a href=\"Conviction\"&gt;Conviction&lt;/a&gt; aura, to maximize lightning damage and help \"break\" monster lightning immmunity.\nIn \"Lord of Destruction\", because monsters in &lt;a href=\"Hell%20difficulty\"&gt;Hell difficulty&lt;/a&gt; have vast health reserves and often have high &lt;a href=\"resistances\"&gt;resistances&lt;/a&gt; or immunities, Fist of the Heavens is not very effective in PvE; however, it shines in PvP duels. In \"\", Fist of the Heavens was greatly improved in PvE as holy bolts now damage both undead and demonic creatures. As the vast majority of enemies in \"Diablo II\" are either undead or demonic, this makes Fist of the Heavens viable in most areas. \nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 25"}
{"id": "24516", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24516", "title": "Fist of the Heavens (Diablo III)", "text": "Fist of the Heavens is a Secondary\u00a0 skill, based on the &lt;a href=\"Fist%20of%20the%20Heavens%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Paladin skill of the same name&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nWhen cast, strikes the targeted location anywhere within 60 yards. Can be cast over walls and terrain. The &lt;a href=\"charged%20bolt\"&gt;charged bolt&lt;/a&gt;s are released evenly in 6 directions, and travel up to 40 yards, piercing through enemies. Each of the sparks deals full damage.\nDevelopment.\nThe ability was the first one to be completed for the Crusader, in terms of how the skill worked and its supporting art."}
