{"id": "4863", "revid": "48080954", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4863", "title": "Fists of Fire", "text": "Fists of Fire is an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Combining her powerful Martial Arts abilities with her psychic training, an Assassin can charge her own fists with pyrokinetic energies, scorching her opponents when the charge is released. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nThis ability is a &lt;a href=\"Charge-up%20Skill\"&gt;Charge-up Skill&lt;/a&gt;. If just one charge is released, it deals fire damage in a small radius. If two charges are released, it deals an explosion in a larger radius. Releasing three charges causes an explosion and a patch of flame, similar to Amazon's &lt;a href=\"Immolation%20Arrow\"&gt;Immolation Arrow&lt;/a&gt; skill, except at close range.\nFists of Fire converts a portion of the user's physical damage into fire damage. The fire damage cannot exceed 100% of the physical damage. Against individual monsters with equal resistances in both types of damage, this skill is of little use. However, its area of effect potential makes it useful against groups of monsters. At level 34 or higher, this skill converts \"all\" physical damage to fire damage, which can be problematic when using it in conjunction with &lt;a href=\"Cobra%20Strike\"&gt;Cobra Strike&lt;/a&gt;: the latter skill only leeches life and mana based on physical damage dealt.\nFists of Fire it a valuable synergy for &lt;a href=\"Phoenix%20Strike\"&gt;Phoenix Strike&lt;/a&gt;'s first charge, and can be used in conjunction with Phoenix Strike. \nThe fire radius value displayed in skill infobox is invalid in D2R (at least up to v2.7) because it can be verified as being still actually 2.6(6) yards in-game (as displayed in base Diablo 2) and not 4 (as shown in D2R). The value \"4\" provided in par1 is given in game units (and still processed as such), which are assumed to be 2/3 yard each, but this was not rewritten in SkillDesc.txt after strings were migrated to new funcs for D2R. Surprisingly, &lt;a href=\"Blades%20of%20Ice\"&gt;Blades of Ice&lt;/a&gt; had the value recalculated properly as par1*2/3 using desc func 36 in D2R.\nSkill Progression.\nMana Cost: 2\nCharge 3 burn duration: 2.56 seconds (straight from miss('fistsoffirefirewall'.rang) in game frames)"}
{"id": "24582", "revid": "43723075", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24582", "title": "Fists of Thunder", "text": "Fists of Thunder is a Primary\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Monk%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt; skill. It is reminiscent of the classic &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt;'s skill &lt;a href=\"Fists%20of%20Fire\"&gt;Fists of Fire&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nWhen the enemy is targeted with Fists of Thunder, if the Monk is not at close combat distance, he/she will &lt;a href=\"teleport\"&gt;teleport&lt;/a&gt; to them (can teleport for up to 20 yards, can pass through enemies and allies, but not through impassable obstacles). The first two hits deal damage to the primary target only, but the last hit splits damage among all enemies in a 6 yard sphere in front of the monk, centered on the primary target.\nAs with other Combo skills, to gain the third hit, Monk does not need to hit the same target three times or even stand in one place: the hits just need to be done within a reasonable time.\nThis skill generates Spirit faster than other primary skills.\nDevelopment.\nThe skill was originally called \"Hands of Lightning.\" It generated 3 Spirit per hit, or 9 per combo, and then 6 per hit and 18 per combo.\nIn the interim between the release of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" and its &lt;a href=\"Reaper%20of%20Souls\"&gt;expansion&lt;/a&gt;, it was found that Thunderclap was the ability's most popular &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Rune\"&gt;Skill Rune&lt;/a&gt; due to its teleport ability. For \"Reaper of Souls\", all of the other Skill Runes of this ability gained this property.\nStatic Charge in 2.3 affected \"all\" enemies hit by any Monk with this skill, being incredibly potent if taken by multiple Monks in a group. In 2.4, this is fixed to only affect enemies hit by the Monk themselves."}
