{"id": "38717", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38717", "title": "Flame Shield", "text": "Flame Shield\u00a0is a Defensive Fire spell used by\u00a0 in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nThis spell works similarly to &lt;a href=\"Serenity\"&gt;Serenity&lt;/a&gt; in that it grants a complete immunity to all damage and effects for a very short time, and then recharges for quite some time. Likewise it can always be cast, even under &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt; (removing any) or while performing other actions.\nIt also deals a bit of periodic damage to enemies next to the Sorceress, but its short duration and low damage numbers make it completely ineffective as an offensive tool. Moreover, contrary to the tooltip, enemies damaged by the Flame Shield do \"not\" count as Burning.\nNote that even though it removes any movement-impairing effects, it does \"NOT\" grant the ability to move through enemies unhindered, and as such, the Sorceress can be trapped by a large horde of enemies with little help from this spell."}
{"id": "3882", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3882", "title": "Flame Spider", "text": "Flame Spiders are a type of &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant Spider&lt;/a&gt; with brilliant red carapaces that make them easily distinguishable from their green counterparts. They are typically found in the company of &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Spinner\"&gt;Poison Spinner&lt;/a&gt;s in &lt;a href=\"Arachnid%20Lair\"&gt;Arachnid Lair&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Cavern\"&gt;Spider Cavern&lt;/a&gt;. \nThey start running away at 40% health. They are the most aggressive of the &lt;a href=\"Giant%20Spider\"&gt;Giant spiders&lt;/a&gt;. Flame Spiders have a 40% chance to deal &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; damage."}
{"id": "10088", "revid": "176312", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=10088", "title": "Flame Wave", "text": "Flame Wave is a Fire spell in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\", a variant of .\nGeneral Information.\nThis spell creates a moving wall of flame which quickly travels away from the character. The higher the level, the more damage it does and the wider the wave is (it can be wider than the visible screen at high levels).\nIt deals much more damage than Fire Wall, to compensate for its inability to deal &lt;a href=\"damage%20over%20time\"&gt;damage over time&lt;/a&gt;. However, it is usually losing to , dealing comparable damage, but only once per cast (while Fireball hits the targeted foe twice) and costs about twice as much Mana. Still, Flame Wave can potentially hit more enemies due to its width.\nAnother significant weakness is that there are invisible \"damage gaps\" between the segments of the wave like those in the normal &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Wall%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Fire Wall&lt;/a&gt;, so it may be difficult to hit many monsters with one spell, despite its area damage. \nIn addition, this spell cannot be cast right next to the character, so any enemies at the melee range will not be affected.\nIt can be used to lure out of his lair without fighting his bodyguards. Flame Wave might also be useful during quests such as &lt;a href=\"Skeleton%20King%20%28Quest%29\"&gt;Skeleton King&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Chamber%20of%20Bone\"&gt;Chamber of Bone&lt;/a&gt;.\nThis spell can hit the player who casts it (if they quickly into it), is &lt;a href=\"block\"&gt;block&lt;/a&gt;able, and its damage counts as damage from a trap.\nDamage Calculation:"}
