{"id": "4052", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4052", "title": "Flamebellow", "text": "Flamebellow is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Balrog%20Blade\"&gt;Balrog Blade&lt;/a&gt; from \"\".\nSister to fellow unique &lt;a href=\"Swords\"&gt;sword&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Frostwind\"&gt;Frostwind&lt;/a&gt;, Flamebellow has strong affinities to the &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt; element.\nFlamebellow does very high damage when wielded with either one or two hands, and its added fire damage makes Flamebellow more effective against enemies with low &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Resist\"&gt;Fire Resist&lt;/a&gt;.\nFlamebellow's most unique property is its ability to cast an extremely high level . At high levels, this Inferno can deal a good amount of damage, though it's not very powerful compared to what a &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;' Inferno can achieve. The only problem is that physical fighters often don't have very much &lt;a href=\"mana\"&gt;mana&lt;/a&gt;, so using Inferno could put a bad strain on a fighter's mana.\nFlamebellow is certainly a more offensive than defensive blade. However, it does grant &lt;a href=\"Absorption\"&gt;Absorption&lt;/a&gt; of Fire, which could come in handy considering quite a few enemies use fire attacks.\nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: (40-51) To (202-255)\nTwo-Hand Damage: (148-187) To (318-401)\nRequired Level: 71\nRequired Strength: 185\nRequired Dexterity: 87\nSword Class - "}
