{"id": "1957", "revid": "49424366", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1957", "title": "Flamespike the Crawler", "text": "Flamespike the Crawler was a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique\"&gt;Super Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Razor%20Spine\"&gt;Razor Spine&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Inner%20Cloister\"&gt;Inner Cloister&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"The%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". It is not encountered in the game with \"&lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Destruction%20%28game%29\"&gt;Lord of Destruction&lt;/a&gt;\" expansion pack, though characters from old versions may still run into him.\nFlamespike was the last Quill Rat of any type found in the game. In the original \"Diablo II\", it and his pack of 5 or 6 minions always spawned in the Inner Cloister area, and were usually the only monsters in that area. A lot of the time they spawn almost directly on top of the waypoint there, making it a bit of a hazard to use the teleporting pad.\nFlamespike was recognizable by its bluish green decor, and his Cursed attribute. The combination of his &lt;a href=\"Amplify%20Damage\"&gt;Amplify Damage&lt;/a&gt; and the ranged quills from it and its minions could quickly become lethal, particularly on higher difficulties.\nBonuses:\nTrivia.\nDevelopment.\nOriginally in v1.00-1.06b Flamespike the Crawler had a blue color."}
