{"id": "38801", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38801", "title": "Flay", "text": "Bash\u00a0is a Basic skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nFlay deals less damage than other Basic skills, but adds a &lt;a href=\"Bleed\"&gt;Bleed&lt;/a&gt; effect which stacks (however, each stack will have a separate independent duration). Requires a slashing weapon (&lt;a href=\"Swords\"&gt;Swords&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Axes\"&gt;Axes&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Swords\"&gt;Two-Handed Swords&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed%20Axes\"&gt;Two-Handed Axes&lt;/a&gt;) to be equipped and switches to those when used.\nBleed applied is completely independent from , &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Thirst\"&gt;Blood Thirst&lt;/a&gt; and other Bleed effects.\nRemember that Bleed effects cannot roll &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt;s, but instead are increased in damage proportionally to the Critical Hit Chance/Damage ratio.\nCounts as Warlord skill."}
{"id": "9505", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9505", "title": "Flayed One", "text": "Flayed Ones are the final and most powerful &lt;a href=\"Overlord%20%28Diablo%20I%29\"&gt;Overlord&lt;/a&gt; variant in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20I\"&gt;Diablo I&lt;/a&gt;\". They appear on the final levels of the caves. Their strength and stamina exceeds their lesser kin by far, they also have a resistance to &lt;a href=\"Magic\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and immunity to &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "39338", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=39338", "title": "Flayed One (Diablo III)", "text": "Flayed Ones were large &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s that were tortured and their skin torn off to be used to create structures. They were kept in a state of perpetual torment, screaming as chains tore their flesh.\n&lt;a href=\"The%20Nephalem\"&gt;The Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; saw them whilst traveling through the sin towers in the &lt;a href=\"Arreat%20Crater\"&gt;Arreat Crater&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nFlayed Ones appear in the Arreat Crater zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". However, they appear purely in the background. They are only properly named and described by &lt;a href=\"Eirena\"&gt;Eirena&lt;/a&gt; if she acts as a &lt;a href=\"follower\"&gt;follower&lt;/a&gt; in the zone."}
{"id": "24551", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24551", "title": "Flayer", "text": "The Flayer is a &lt;a href=\"Normal%20Items\"&gt;Normal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ceremonial%20Knives\"&gt;ceremonial knife&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIt requires character level 35 to be used.\nStats.\nFlayerCeremonial Knife"}
{"id": "24576", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24576", "title": "Flayer (Diablo III)", "text": ""}
{"id": "3506", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3506", "title": "Flayer Dungeon", "text": "The Flayer Dungeon is the location where you will find &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Brain\"&gt;Khalim's Brain&lt;/a&gt;. It is found in the middle of the small Flayer village in the &lt;a href=\"Flayer%20Jungle\"&gt;Flayer Jungle&lt;/a&gt;, where &lt;a href=\"The%20Gidbinn%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;The Gidbinn&lt;/a&gt; can be found.\nThis area is a dungeon style location found in the Flayer Jungle. It consists of three levels, the final of these containing a &lt;a href=\"Golden%20Chest\"&gt;golden chest&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Heart\"&gt;Khalim's Heart&lt;/a&gt; inside. The chest is guarded by the &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Enchanted\"&gt;Fire Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor%20Endugu\"&gt;Witch Doctor Endugu&lt;/a&gt; and his &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20Shaman\"&gt;cohorts&lt;/a&gt;. Once the Brain is taken, the chest will contain random magic items the next time it is opened."}
{"id": "3492", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3492", "title": "Flayer Jungle", "text": "The Flayer Jungle is another jungle zone in &lt;a href=\"The%20Infernal%20Gate\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt;. The zone can sometimes be accessed from the &lt;a href=\"Spider%20Forest\"&gt;Spider Forest&lt;/a&gt;, or more often from the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Marsh\"&gt;Great Marsh&lt;/a&gt;. As its name suggests, the zone is infested by &lt;a href=\"Fetish\"&gt;Flayers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Killer\"&gt;Soul Killer&lt;/a&gt;s and their &lt;a href=\"Fetish%20Shaman\"&gt;shamans&lt;/a&gt;.\nSomewhere in a random location, the player can find guarded by a random unique &lt;a href=\"Fetish\"&gt;Flayer&lt;/a&gt;. This item is necessary to complete the quest. The Gidbinn may or may not be found near the entrance to the &lt;a href=\"Flayer%20Dungeon\"&gt;Flayer Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. The Flayer Jungle houses another optional dungeon, the &lt;a href=\"Swampy%20Pit\"&gt;Swampy Pit&lt;/a&gt; with &lt;a href=\"waypoint\"&gt;waypoint&lt;/a&gt; near.\nUsually the Gidbinn can be found near or inside a Flayer village. The village consists of several huts made out of wood. A cooking pot with several humanoid corpses inside can be found there as well.\nSomewhere in the Flayer Jungle lies the entrance into the &lt;a href=\"Flayer%20Dungeon\"&gt;Flayer Dungeon&lt;/a&gt;. Players need to explore the maze-like dungeon in order to obtain &lt;a href=\"Khalim%27s%20Brain\"&gt;Khalim's Brain&lt;/a&gt;. The golden chest containing the Brain is guarded by the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor%20Endugu\"&gt;Witch Doctor Endugu&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe end of the Flayer Jungle is guarded by &lt;a href=\"Stormtree\"&gt;Stormtree&lt;/a&gt; and his minions."}
