{"id": "32743", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=32743", "title": "Flesh Harvester", "text": "The Flesh Harvester is a crab-like &lt;a href=\"Animals\"&gt;beast&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; type found in &lt;a href=\"Tidal%20Cave\"&gt;Tidal Cave&lt;/a&gt; beneath the &lt;a href=\"Greyhollow%20Island\"&gt;Greyhollow Island&lt;/a&gt; (, &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt;), introduced in patch 2.4 of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn-game.\nFlesh Harvesters are never encountered in large numbers (even two in one place are a rare sight), but are often accompanied by hordes of &lt;a href=\"Amputator\"&gt;Amputator&lt;/a&gt;s. They are extremely slow (even compared to other large and slow enemies), but their huge &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; pool makes them durable. In melee, they attack with slow, but very powerful claw pinches.\nApparently, these creatures are enslaved by &lt;a href=\"Abyssal\"&gt;Abyssal&lt;/a&gt;s.\nDevelopment.\nOriginally, there were supposed to be at least 3 color skins, as evidenced by artwork, but only one made it into the game."}
