{"id": "37732", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37732", "title": "Flesh Thing", "text": "The Flesh Things are &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;s that appear in \"\". They can be found in the final two levels of the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Crypts\"&gt;Crypt&lt;/a&gt; (3-4).\nFlesh Things are aptly-named, for they are weird unholy conglomerations of parts seemingly thrown together at random. They have two heads, a long, tentacle-like appendage for one arm, a pulpy, earthworm-like torso with a vertical mouth, and one leg is so short and twisted the creatures can only walk with the aid of a squeaky flesh roller that functions as one of its feet. (this is the source of the eerie, squeaking noise they make when walking to battle).\nWeak and disfigured though they are, Flesh Beasts have the most hit points in the game, have resistances to every element, and take a great deal of punishment before finally succumbing to the inevitable."}
