{"id": "22724", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22724", "title": "Depth Diggers", "text": "The Depth Diggers are &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"pants\"&gt;pants&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". They require &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60 to drop.\nThese are a very good choice for protection, due to their guaranteed &lt;a href=\"resistance\"&gt;resistance&lt;/a&gt;s bonus.\nThe unique affix damage boost stacks multiplicatively with other similar effects.\nOriginally, the legendary affix only worked with primary skills that generate resource. However, this was changed in patch 2.7.2 to affect all primary skills, including ones that do not generate resource, such as those of &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Doctor\"&gt;Witch Doctor&lt;/a&gt;s.\nDamage is increased even if the player is at maximum resource already, and will also stack with the &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Gem\"&gt;Legendary Gem&lt;/a&gt; named &lt;a href=\"Simplicity%27s%20Strength\"&gt;Simplicity's Strength&lt;/a&gt;. As such, if the player does most of their damage from their Primary skills (like, for example, a &lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt; utilizing &lt;a href=\"Shenlong%27s%20Spirit\"&gt;Shenlong's Spirit&lt;/a&gt;), they may be wise to don this pair and receive a great deal of attack power."}
