{"id": "41824", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41824", "title": "Desert Crawler", "text": "Desert Crawlers (also called Desert Scorpions) are a type of scorpid creature found in the &lt;a href=\"Shassar%20Sea\"&gt;Shassar Sea&lt;/a&gt;. Their stingers are laced with a deadly &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; that can kill within minutes after impalement. They bury beneath the sands, lying in wait to strike at unsuspecting travelers. Their chitin is toxic to the touch, and is tough enough to use to make armor.\nThe Crawlers are apparently aggressive\u2014so much so that their presence stymied &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;'s plans to open trade with the region. Later, Westmarch offered &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt; to those who could clear the region of these creatures.\nTheir venom can be used to make a concoction that can cure hallucinations. It has been described to be like \"a swift punch the brain\", by those unlucky to sniff it.\nIn-game.\nDesert Crawlers are scorpion-like found in the Shassar Sea zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Sub-zones include the &lt;a href=\"Oasis%20of%20No%20Return\"&gt;Oasis of No Return&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ruins%20of%20Greater%20Fahira\"&gt;Ruins of Greater Fahira&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Prison%20of%20the%20Scorpion\"&gt;Prison of the Scorpion&lt;/a&gt;. It can also be used to make ink."}
