{"id": "22018", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22018", "title": "Development Hell", "text": "Development Hell is a new way of showing the credits, it is a rarely spawned level that features a group of zombies with the names of the \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" game developers.\n\"Development Hell\" is a reference to , an abnormally long period of development for computer games or other various forms of electronic media.\nLocation.\nDevelopment Hell is found in the &lt;a href=\"Cemetery%20of%20the%20Forsaken\"&gt;Cemetery of the Forsaken&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", as one of the &lt;a href=\"Defiled%20Crypt\"&gt;Defiled Crypt&lt;/a&gt;s. It will appear as a fourth accessible passage, as opposed to normal three, and will have the Development Hell name instead of Defiled Crypt.\nThe chance for it to appear is very low (roughly 1%).\nMonsters.\nThis crypt features a variety of zombies:\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Ravenous%20Dead\"&gt;Ravenous Dead&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Retching%20Cadaver\"&gt;Retching Cadaver&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Hungry%20Corpse\"&gt;Hungry Corpse&lt;/a&gt;s. All monsters have the names and jobs of the game developing group. Two unique monsters are present in this dungeon: &lt;a href=\"Jay%20Wilson%20%28monster%29\"&gt;Jay Wilson&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Josh%20Mosqueira%20%28monster%29\"&gt;Josh Mosqueira&lt;/a&gt;.\nUnique rewards include &lt;a href=\"Transmogrification\"&gt;Transmogrification&lt;/a&gt;-only swords, &lt;a href=\"Incinerator\"&gt;Incinerator&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rancor\"&gt;Rancor&lt;/a&gt;.\nAchievements.\nKilling Jay Wilson grants a hidden achievement; \"Smash, Jay, Smash\", placed in \"Feat of Strength\" group on the achievement page, plus a sigil of a horned &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;."}
