{"id": "45633", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45633", "title": "Devmir", "text": "Devmir was a resident of &lt;a href=\"Nevesk\"&gt;Nevesk&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt;, Devmir was among those who attended a service at the Nevesk chapel. &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt; appeared, seducing him and the other villagers into following her. While the priest urged them to resist Lilith, &lt;a href=\"Vani\"&gt;Vani&lt;/a&gt; took a Cathedral emblem and bashes him in the head. While the priest was speaking to Vani, Devmir plunged a knife into his back. Devmir and the townsfolk continued to assault the priest as Lilith left. They placed the headless body in &lt;a href=\"Icehowl%20Ruins\"&gt;Icehowl Ruins&lt;/a&gt;, where &lt;a href=\"Iosef\"&gt;Iosef&lt;/a&gt; later found it. Upon Iosef's arrival into Nevesk, Devmir and the townsfolk drugged Iosef and locked him in a shed. \n investigated the ruins and survived, much to the surprise of the villagers, Devmir included. They posed a celebration in order to drug the Wanderer. They succeeded, but the Wanderer escaped with the aid of Iosef. Devmir and the other villagers attacked them, but were killed in the fight.\nIn-game.\nDevmir is an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". He is first introduced inside the tavern in &lt;a href=\"Nevesk\"&gt;Nevesk&lt;/a&gt;, as part of the \"&lt;a href=\"Dusk%20on%20the%20Mountain\"&gt;Dusk on the Mountain&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found by the fireplace in the tavern. During &lt;a href=\"A%20Hero%27s%20Reward\"&gt;A Hero's Reward&lt;/a&gt;, he becomes a &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;. As a monster, he uses an &lt;a href=\"axes\"&gt;axe&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuotes.\nDuring &lt;a href=\"Dusk%20on%20the%20Mountain\"&gt;Dusk on the Mountain&lt;/a&gt;, before entering &lt;a href=\"Icehowl%20Ruins\"&gt;Icehowl Ruins&lt;/a&gt;. He can be found standing next to the fireplace in the tavern. "}
{"id": "35185", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=35185", "title": "Devour", "text": "Devour is a Corpse skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It very loosely resembles the &lt;a href=\"Carrion%20Vine\"&gt;Carrion Vine&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Solar%20Creeper\"&gt;Solar Creeper&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nWhen cast, consumes all nearby &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;s (radius is wide enough to affect the entire screen) to replenish the Necromancer's &lt;a href=\"Essence\"&gt;Essence&lt;/a&gt;.\nCorpses are not devoured all at once, but rather in rapid succession, roughly 3-4 per second.\nThe skill costs no &lt;a href=\"Essence\"&gt;Essence&lt;/a&gt; to cast, and has no &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt;, so with sufficient corpses, it can be used again and again.\nDevelopment.\nThe logic behind the Necromancer's Devour skill was that though it can feel wasteful, the decision to consume all the corpses is intentional, so Devour isn't used mindlessly."}
